(93, 3, 9, NULL, 8, 3, 115, '2021-06-17', '2935', 'M&E Manager Kenya', 'Plantation Manager', 'Head Office', 'Forestry', 'Tree stock data from accounts', 'Major', '<p>There is 5.2% less trees in the accounts data for compartment A043 in Kiambere. 131 trees were not counted in the compartment due to bad demarcation.</p><p>Compartment A035 has 11 trees more although the demarcation was correct.</p>', 'closed', '2021-06-22', NULL, '2021-07-08', '2021-07-16', '2021-07-05', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-06-17 13:58:06', '2021-07-18 15:04:23'),
(94, 8, 11, NULL, 8, 19, NULL, '2021-06-17', '863', 'Executive Director Forestry', 'Site Manager Plantation Nyongoro', 'Nyongoro', 'Forestry', 'Task results 29th May to 4th June', 'Major', '<p>1. Result not input in the front office: Activity 20641 NYO-Perm-Maint-Pruning (mech) result was not inputted on 4th June 2021 by the forest technician.</p><ol><li>2. Inputting of wrong results for 20641 NYO-Perm-Maint-Pruning&gt;2mtrs (3LL) on 4th June and 3rd June 2021 by the forest technician,</li><li>&nbsp;</li><li>3. Inputting of wrong results for 20644 NYO-Temp-Maint-Cleaning manual on 31st May 2021 that resulted in the temporary staff not getting a bonus.</li></ol><p>4. Failure to communicate after the breakdown of mechanized pruning saw on 2nd June 2021 for the workers to be reallocated another task within the system.</p>', 'closed', '2021-06-24', NULL, '2021-07-08', '2021-07-31', '2021-07-05', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-06-17 18:31:19', '2021-07-12 07:39:08'),
(95, 18, 13, NULL, 8, 18, 116, '2021-06-20', '2450', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks', 'Site Manager Farmers Programme 7Forks', '7 Forks', 'Forestry', '7 forks stock summary detail report for May week one to June week 2.', 'Major', '<p>There\'s a variation in tree stock in 9 out of the 13 farmers checked.</p><p>The document used for comparison was 7fork stock summary for May and June 2021.</p><p>Example of &nbsp;the farmers with the tree stock variation are;</p><p>1.Angelinah Nzanzai Munyoki - 89 trees.</p><p>2.Jackline Mueni kitale &nbsp;- 158 trees.</p><p>3 Francis Mutunga Mati +13 trees.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2021-06-23', NULL, '2021-09-13', '2021-10-30', '2021-07-05', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-06-20 11:17:12', '2021-12-15 15:14:23'),
(96, 19, 11, NULL, 8, 19, 118, '2021-06-21', '1238', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer Nyongoro', 'Site Manager Plantation Nyongoro', 'Nyongoro', 'Forestry', 'Compartments grid, coordinates and map.', 'Major', '<p>There were 5 beacons that were are off the coordinates. These 5 beacons were found in 3 compartments that tree count verification was done. These beacons were # 968, 279, 348, 555, and 624.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2021-06-22', NULL, '2021-08-01', '2021-08-31', '2021-07-05', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-06-21 09:07:31', '2021-11-18 07:25:27'),
(97, 19, 11, NULL, 8, 19, 119, '2021-06-21', '7994', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer Nyongoro', 'Site Manager Plantation Nyongoro', 'Nyongoro', 'Forestry', 'M&E tree tree count verification data and accounts tree tree count data.', 'Major', '<p><a href=\"https://car.betterglobeforestry.co.ke/View/38/file\">https://car.betterglobeforestry.co.ke/View/38/file</a></p><p>There is variances in the number of &nbsp;trees counted by M&amp;E compared to the number that are in accounts.&nbsp;</p><p>Tree counting verification exercise done from 31st May to 4th June found out variances of 2.6%, 9.4%, 16.1% 18.4% and 0.4% for A064, D083, G104, I044 and E021 respectively.</p>', 'closed', '2021-06-23', NULL, '2021-07-08', '2021-11-30', '2021-07-05', 'To check and redo the boundaries of all compartments. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-06-21 09:42:15', '2022-01-21 15:48:12'),
(98, 3, 29, NULL, 23, 3, NULL, '2021-06-24', '5137', 'M&E Manager Kenya', 'Operations Manager', 'Head Office', 'Operations', 'Plantation protection', 'Major', '<p>There was livestock found in compartments A046 on 24/6/2021. A calf was tied to a Mukau tree. This causes injury to the bark of the trees. The calf was tied overnight.&nbsp;</p><p>Other trees had bark injuries from before. The patrol of the security is not sufficient</p><p><a href=\"https://1drv.ms/w/s!As25tzmT79Zig9UiS9vCxqzpvLISzw?e=4Vlj0f\">Report</a></p>', 'closed', '2021-06-28', NULL, '2021-07-19', '2021-07-31', '2021-06-28', 'Head of security is definitely not doing his job! To look into the circumstances and stop this once and for all! Kindly present creative solutions this week!', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-06-24 14:21:33', '2021-07-22 13:27:54'),
(99, 2, 26, NULL, 8, 2, NULL, '2021-06-28', '8569', 'M&E Manager Uganda', 'Site Manager Dokolo', 'Dokolo', 'Forestry', 'Farmer list', 'Major', '<p>Farmers information is correct but didn\'t receive trees</p><p>Wrong numbers</p><p>Most numbers are for CR\'s and they complain about non payment</p><p>Some seedlings given are mixed with local species instead of the recommended improved species</p><p>Seedlings are distributed in the dry season hence high mortality</p>', 'closed', '2021-06-28', NULL, '2021-07-08', '2021-11-30', '2021-07-05', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-06-28 09:13:19', '2022-08-10 16:26:56'),
(100, 18, 13, NULL, 8, 18, NULL, '2021-06-29', '1888', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks', 'Site Manager Farmers Programme 7Forks', '7 Forks', 'Forestry', 'M&E farmers to verification list for June 2021.', 'Minor', '<ol><li>1.Incorrect phone number for two farmers.</li><li>Rosetina kivinya Ngula</li><li>James Mwangangi Muthangya</li></ol><p>2. 5 farmers phone numbers that goes directly to a different person from the one &nbsp;provided in the list.</p><p>Jane Njoka Ngari.</p><p>Petronillah Mutua Kea</p><p>Beatrice Muli Savi</p><p>Kithumbi Mutua Mbithi</p><p>Joseph Mwendwa Maluki.</p><p>3.5 farmers are unreachable &nbsp;completely.</p><p>Alex Ngonda Nzenge</p><p>Kyalo Kitemi</p><p>Munyoki Mwasya Muthui</p><p>Damaris Nzambi Mutua</p><p>Perminas kiurah Nyaga.</p><p>Impact;In future, farmers payment that shall be made via mpesa might be ineffective&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2021-06-29', NULL, '2021-08-03', '2021-08-31', '2021-08-02', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-06-29 09:18:46', '2022-03-21 18:49:15'),
(101, 19, 11, NULL, 8, 19, 127, '2021-07-02', '4039', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer Nyongoro', 'Site Manager Plantation Nyongoro', 'Nyongoro', 'Forestry', 'Work Instructions', 'Major', '<p>Work instructions used for forestry activities are in editable word formats and with no signatures.</p><p>Work instruction for both Nursery and plantations have no signatures hence it is difficult to tell if they are approved. <a href=\"https://webmail.betterglobeforestry.com/Mondo/lang/sys/Forms/MAI/GetAttachment.aspx?&amp;MessageID=3EA9A431B29949A588D1C6F989316F68.MAI&amp;Folder=%2FInbox&amp;Filename=Work%20instruction%20for%20tree%20counting%201705.docx&amp;Seq=1\">https://webmail.betterglobeforestry.com/Mondo/lang/sys/Forms/MAI/GetAttachment.aspx?&amp;MessageID=3EA9A431B29949A588D1C6F989316F68.MAI&amp;Folder=%2FInbox&amp;Filename=Work%20instruction%20for%20tree%20counting%201705.docx&amp;Seq=1</a></p><p>Good example of an approved documents are the ones for HR on Health and safety policies. These documents are in pdf and have been signed and dates indicated. It is therefore possible to confidently say that the document is approved.</p>', 'closed', '2021-08-12', NULL, '2021-09-29', '2021-10-01', '2021-09-28', 'this is being handled by the QC', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-07-02 20:05:58', '2021-09-29 14:33:04'),
(102, 2, 26, NULL, 8, 2, NULL, '2021-07-05', '2699', 'M&E Manager Uganda', 'Site Manager Dokolo', 'Dokolo', 'Forestry', 'Variance between the number of trees reported by AAs and the number of trees reported by the farmer', 'Minor', '<p>There\'s is a variance between the number of trees reported by AAs and the number of trees reported by the farmer</p><p>Phone numbers recorded on the farmer list are for CRs who claim to have the phone numbers of the farmers and incase you need information. they can easily get it for you from the farmer or village coordinators</p>', 'closed', '2021-07-06', NULL, '2021-09-17', '2021-09-30', '2021-08-02', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-07-05 11:20:24', '2022-02-11 16:24:20'),
(103, 18, 9, NULL, 8, 18, 130, '2021-07-06', '9724', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks', 'Plantation Manager', 'Head Office', 'Forestry', 'Potting work instruction', 'Minor', '<p>Soil scooping during potting was done using hands instead of &nbsp;scooping spoons &nbsp;as per the work instruction on 6/7/2021.A casual might be injured on hands as he/She &nbsp;scoops the soil.</p><p>From the records,8 small shovels were &nbsp;delivered on 20/12/2011 and none of them is available.&nbsp;</p><p><a href=\"https://1drv.ms/w/s!As25tzmT79Zig9ZlW8Nbv3p0BcvyUQ\">https://1drv.ms/w/s!As25tzmT79Zig9ZlW8Nbv3p0BcvyUQ</a></p><p>&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2021-07-21', NULL, '2021-08-03', '2021-08-31', '2021-08-02', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-07-06 22:10:08', '2021-08-30 14:34:36'),
(104, 18, 9, NULL, 8, 18, 131, '2021-07-06', '8957', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks', 'Plantation Manager', 'Head Office', 'Forestry', 'Mukau seedling production work instruction.', 'Minor', '<p>Casuals doing Pricking out without surgical or latex gloves on 6/7/2021.</p><p>Forest Technician\'s comment “ The latex gloves depleted on 3/7/2021 and an IPR was made on Friday\"</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>https://1drv.ms/w/s!As25tzmT79Zig9ZkX44hWXwCEEsntg</p>', 'closed', '2021-07-21', NULL, '2021-08-03', '2021-08-06', '2021-08-02', 'ok', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-07-06 22:23:55', '2021-08-08 13:07:27'),
(105, 18, 9, NULL, 8, 18, NULL, '2021-07-07', '4840', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks', 'Plantation Manager', 'Head Office', 'Forestry', 'Seedling production job card 2021.', 'Minor', '<p>The job cards are being filled late. Pricking out commenced on 3/7/2021 and the job cards were checked on 6/7/2021.</p><p>&nbsp;The job card for tree numbers 568,567,582,556,565,585 and 587 have been filled upto sowing stage on 6/7/2021.</p>', 'closed', '2021-07-21', NULL, '2021-08-03', '2021-08-06', '2021-08-02', 'ok', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-07-07 08:40:30', '2021-08-08 12:47:06');
