(138, 16, 5, NULL, 5, 3, NULL, '2021-10-26', '8497', 'Human resource manager', 'FOD & Quality Coordinator', 'Head Office', 'Operations', 'FOD,HRM and OM interaction meeting', 'Major', '<p>During the meeting, it was clear that some staff are sending requests and purchases to OM at the last minute. This has caused delays in other operations.</p>', 'closed', '2021-10-29', NULL, '2021-11-11', '2021-11-12', '2021-11-06', 'This has been done through the HODs', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-10-26 20:26:15', '2021-11-19 16:15:55'),
(139, 16, 8, NULL, 8, 3, NULL, '2021-10-26', '3531', 'Human resource manager', 'Executive Director Forestry', 'Head Office', 'Forestry', 'Kiambere site Loss of 1000seedlings poisoned', 'Major', '<ol><li>1.There is no plan for the forestry department &nbsp;for daily/weekly task allocation</li><li>2. One PMS gets the title of Head of the nursery without authorization</li></ol>', 'closed', '2021-11-19', NULL, '2021-11-19', '2021-11-22', '2021-11-19', 'Done', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-10-26 20:36:44', '2021-11-19 16:14:31'),
(140, 19, 22, NULL, 5, 19, NULL, '2021-10-28', '5464', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer Nyongoro', 'Site logistics Officer Nyongoro', 'Nyongoro', 'Operations', 'Electric Fence Installation', 'Major', '<p>Destructions to the already installed cables have slowed down the electrical fence cabling process. Slow progress is a result of the repairs which must be done to alow flow of current to the whole length of the already installed section.</p><p>The Destructions by wild animals also resulted in short circuiting leading to automatic disconnection of power at the control. This situation increases the risk of the intact sections &nbsp;being destroyed.</p>', 'closed', '2021-11-01', NULL, '2022-01-17', '2022-01-21', '2022-01-13', 'The work instruction was developed and the power supply for the fence optimized.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-10-28 13:31:20', '2022-01-22 14:42:33'),
(141, 5, 22, NULL, 5, 19, NULL, '2021-11-06', '7344', 'FOD & Quality Coordinator', 'Site logistics Officer Nyongoro', 'Nyongoro', 'Operations', 'Report by SLO', 'Major', '<p>Damage of the Bulldozer during Squatters eviction</p>', 'closed', '2021-11-16', NULL, '2022-01-17', '2022-06-30', '2022-01-13', 'ok', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-11-06 13:19:10', '2022-07-26 17:16:34'),
(142, 5, 22, NULL, 5, 19, NULL, '2021-11-06', '8449', 'FOD & Quality Coordinator', 'Site logistics Officer Nyongoro', 'Nyongoro', 'Operations', 'Report by SLO', 'Major', '<p>Accident and damage of our Trailer during water transportation to Dide waride village for donation.</p>', 'closed', '2021-11-16', NULL, '2022-01-17', '2022-01-28', '2022-01-13', 'The CA for this NC was poor preventive maintenance. The cause of the accident on a flat ground clearly shows the wheel axle broke causing it to bend on one side hence causing the accident.\nWe have also started buying water from water suppliers.\nThe Trailer shall be used only in the plantation for filed activities.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-11-06 13:20:39', '2022-02-28 00:31:09'),
(143, 3, 28, NULL, 5, 3, NULL, '2021-11-10', '3284', 'M&E Manager Kenya', 'Site Logistic Manager Dokolo', 'Dokolo', 'Operations', 'Health and Safety: PPE replacement policy', 'Major', '<ol><li>HR policy of PPE replacement requires 6 months for overalls and 4 Months for Gumboots<ol><li>There old PPE’s in the PPE store. Some are torn and discolored.<ol><li>58 Overalls have lasted for more than 2 years on site.</li><li>Last IPR written for 50 pieces on 6th May 2021- Status Commented. Wait for evaluation to be done.</li><li>Last communication: It shall be procured 1 month to production.</li></ol></li><li>There are 10 helmets on site, 4 of which are damaged.</li><li>There is no gas mask and gloves to spray Glyphosate in the nursery.</li><li>Helmets and Gas masks are Highly essential</li></ol></li></ol>', 'closed', '2021-11-11', NULL, '2022-01-17', '2022-01-28', '2022-01-13', 'The corrective action given to submit multiple iprs is wrong. \nWe have bought PPE for the current work force 13people. The rest of PPE we have delayed to buy Just in time. \nThey shall be bought one month before we go to production to be used by workers.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-11-10 17:51:25', '2022-01-19 16:30:01'),
(144, 3, 28, NULL, 5, 3, NULL, '2021-11-10', '4355', 'M&E Manager Kenya', 'Site Logistic Manager Dokolo', 'Dokolo', 'Operations', 'Operations maintenance app', 'Major', '<ol><li>There are 2 seats without arm rests in the office:</li><li>The timber holding roof of the office are being bored into by beetles.&nbsp;</li><li>The parts need to observed and maintained.<ol><li>None are in the preventive maintenance application&nbsp;</li></ol></li></ol>', 'closed', '2021-11-11', NULL, '2022-01-17', '2022-01-28', '2022-01-13', 'The correction has been done and the Office maintenance has been added to the preventive maintenance.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-11-10 17:57:59', '2022-01-25 20:02:33'),
(145, 3, 28, NULL, 5, 3, NULL, '2021-11-10', '1135', 'M&E Manager Kenya', 'Site Logistic Manager Dokolo', 'Dokolo', 'Operations', 'Operations, stock: Chemical waste disposal', 'Major', '<ol><li>Approvals of procedure for chemical disposal took too long.&nbsp;</li><li>Procedure for expired chemical disposal was submitted by SLM in 2020 for expired chemicals to be disposed but nothing has moved yet.&nbsp;</li><li>It has taken almost 1 year and expired chemicals are still in stock</li></ol>', 'closed', '2021-11-11', NULL, '2022-01-17', '2022-01-28', '2022-01-13', 'The chemicals are not in stock because of lack of a disposal procedure. The recomendation from EDF that these chemicals can still be used.\nHowever we have worked on the procedure and up for approval and shall be available in the Document control app.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-11-10 18:08:03', '2022-04-05 16:49:56'),
(146, 3, 28, NULL, 5, 3, NULL, '2021-11-10', '4045', 'M&E Manager Kenya', 'Site Logistic Manager Dokolo', 'Dokolo', 'Operations', 'Work instructions', 'Major', '<p>The weeds in the nursery area have sprouted only a month after the application of glyphosate which renders it ineffective against weeds.</p><p>No work instruction for glyphosate for the nursery technician to use in spraying weeds in the nursery: The technician uses the guides in the bottle.</p><ol><li>&nbsp;</li></ol>', 'closed', '2021-11-11', NULL, '2022-01-17', '2022-02-04', '2022-01-13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-11-10 18:17:25', '2022-04-05 16:48:40'),
(147, 3, 26, NULL, 8, 3, NULL, '2021-11-13', '5594', 'M&E Manager Kenya', 'Site Manager Dokolo', 'Dokolo', 'Forestry', 'Low survival of trees in Farms', 'Major', '<ol><li>Low survival of trees: Up to zero</li><li>The average survival of trees in 35 farms verified is 23.5 trees<ol><li>The main cause of mortality as stated by farmers with very low survival is late distribution past the rain season. Late distribution is considered to be beyond March.</li><li>This occurred in 2018, 2019 and the gapping of trees in 2020.</li><li>The farmers acknowledge that the area is wet but also during dry season the temperature is very high for young trees to survive.</li><li>3 farmers out of 35 lost their trees from the lake Kwania submerging their homesteads.</li></ol></li></ol>', 'closed', '2021-11-13', NULL, '2021-11-19', '2022-12-30', '2021-11-19', NULL, 'There is need to follow the required steps in planting with farmers.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-11-13 08:19:05', '2022-04-05 16:47:47'),
(148, 3, 26, NULL, 8, 3, NULL, '2021-11-13', '4767', 'M&E Manager Kenya', 'Site Manager Dokolo', 'Dokolo', 'Forestry', 'Farmers database: Incorrect GPS coordinates of farms', 'Major', '<p>There are farmers whose GPS coordinates are incorrect.&nbsp;</p><p>3 coordinates led us to other farms that belonged to other farms</p><p>18 farmers GPS coordinates are located completely outside the District areas</p>', 'closed', '2021-11-13', NULL, '2021-11-29', '2021-11-30', '2021-11-19', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-11-13 08:26:56', '2022-04-05 16:46:43'),
(149, 3, 26, NULL, 8, 3, NULL, '2021-11-13', '1536', 'M&E Manager Kenya', 'Site Manager Dokolo', 'Dokolo', 'Forestry', 'Outgrowers Manual: Pruning of trees', 'Major', '<p>32 Farmers had not implemented pruning.&nbsp;</p><p>All the three farmers that had implemented pruning used a Panga instead of pruning saws which were given to the group leaders.</p><p>28 Farmers confirmed that they had not been trained for pruning.</p><p>Only 3 out of the 7 Farmers that had been trained had implemented pruning. 4 that had not implemented cited that they lack pruning saw.</p><p>The trees need Urgent Pruning as they grow very fast.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2021-11-13', NULL, '2021-11-19', '2021-11-26', '2021-11-19', 'The focus now is not on pruning or Training. We shall embark on this once we have corrected our figures , data about the farmers and knowing where they are.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-11-13 08:37:43', '2021-11-19 16:10:36'),
(150, 23, 4, NULL, 23, 3, NULL, '2021-11-17', '3191', 'Managing Director', 'Communication Manager', 'Head Office', 'Communications', 'Weekly follow up on meetings and control if issues are being addressed at the right level', 'Major', '<p>Supposed to receive minutes of meetings. If there are obstacles they need to be discussed upfront in the MT. If given excuses AFTER they are REASONS WHY NOT! There is a problem here both on giving reasons and on communication!&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2021-11-19', NULL, '2022-01-26', '2022-01-27', '2022-01-26', 'Follow up is happening with visible improvements.', 'OK. Kindly follow up carefully so that the corrective action is truly implemented. Checked on 12/8 and this week all seems OK. CM will continue to monitor weekly but this CAR has been adressed succesfully.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-11-17 09:39:32', '2022-01-26 18:14:54'),
(151, 4, 5, NULL, 5, 3, NULL, '2021-11-17', '1254', 'Communication Manager', 'FOD & Quality Coordinator', 'Head Office', 'Operations', 'Nyongoro Site visit', 'Major', '<p>Supervisors wait until field visits from HO personnel, to ask or raise issues that should be addressed, beforehand/immediately.</p>', 'closed', '2021-11-24', NULL, '2022-01-17', '2022-01-21', '2022-01-13', 'This has been communicated to the managers. The next phase shall be to handle any Non-conformances through the HR.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-11-17 10:01:21', '2022-01-19 15:06:05'),
(152, 4, 8, NULL, 8, 3, NULL, '2021-11-17', '5827', 'Communication Manager', 'Executive Director Forestry', 'Head Office', 'Forestry', 'Nyongoro site visit', 'Major', '<p>Supervisors wait until field visits from HO personnel, to ask or raise issues that should be addressed, beforehand/immediately.</p>', 'closed', '2021-11-19', NULL, '2021-11-22', '2021-12-31', '2021-11-20', 'This is a continuous issue that is being addressed at all levels through training in leadership and communication by comms DPT.', 'Communication training was done in the working party: A flow chart for upward and downward vertical communications was presented to be cascaded down to the rest of the teams', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-11-17 10:02:07', '2021-12-03 16:58:58'),
(153, 4, 5, NULL, 5, 3, NULL, '2021-11-17', '7513', 'Communication Manager', 'FOD & Quality Coordinator', 'Head Office', 'Operations', 'Nyongoro site visit', 'Minor', '<p>Fearing to share ideas or even maybe issues in the field with the supervisor(i.e sharing innovative ideas they might have in fear of a supervisor taking the idea as his own)</p>', 'closed', '2021-11-24', NULL, '2022-01-17', '2022-01-28', '2022-01-13', 'The APP is in the planning for IT department this year.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-11-17 10:09:59', '2022-01-19 16:21:45'),
(154, 4, 8, NULL, 8, 19, NULL, '2021-11-17', '104', 'Communication Manager', 'Executive Director Forestry', 'Head Office', 'Forestry', 'Nyongoro site visit ', 'Minor', '<p>Fearing to share ideas or even maybe issues in the field with the supervisor(i.e sharing innovative ideas they might have in fear of a supervisor taking the idea as his own)</p>', 'closed', '2021-11-19', NULL, '2021-11-22', '2021-12-31', '2021-11-20', 'It is also worth noting that staff at all levels are paid to not only follow instructions but giving insight on ways for the company to achieve its objectives hence this policy is not automatic. Staff also can relay their ideas through other channels.', 'This policy is yet to be well understood by staff. Further explanations to be given to staff in forestry meetings  ', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-11-17 10:11:13', '2021-11-29 18:54:33'),
(157, 19, 22, NULL, 5, 19, NULL, '2021-11-18', '348', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer Nyongoro', 'Site logistics Officer Nyongoro', 'Nyongoro', 'Operations', 'Security patrol', 'Major', '<p>Security patrol methods are not sufficient.</p><p>Patrols for Block 4, 5 and 7 are not intensive. This came out after the fire incidences at Block 5&amp;7 on 9th and Block 4 on 10th November when the suspect who was found in the plantation admitted he had set his equipment on the doom palm for three weeks in Block 5. There have been security assigned to patrol block 5 according to the security schedule during the period mentioned by the wine tapper. The Head of the security admitted he learned about the wine tapper\'s presence after the fire incidence.</p><p>The presence of pastoralists who lit fire on part of the buffalo wall at Block 4 is also realised after the fire on 10th November.&nbsp;</p><p>Security schedules for October and November doesn\'t have security guards assigned to Block 7.</p><p>This is because the security schedule was an initiative by SLM to improve on the patrol. Its areas that needed improvement could only be seen during its implementation. Improvement has been done for December schedule and Block 7 which did not appear in November and October has been captured for 7days.&nbsp;</p><p>Security guards also mentioned that far locations of compartments in block 4, 5 and 7 are the barriers to effective patrol since they have been patrolling on foot a situation that limits them from covering all areas.</p>', 'closed', '2021-11-22', NULL, '2022-01-17', '2022-01-28', '2022-01-13', 'Security shall have walkie talkies for communication every 30min to the head of security. They shall patrol and meet at designated areas and exchange information.\nWe have security plan and form to report.\nSecurity training shall be done in Jan-KIA and Feb-NYO', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-11-18 08:00:11', '2022-03-07 16:45:05'),
(158, 19, 22, NULL, 5, 19, NULL, '2021-11-18', '879', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer Nyongoro', 'Site logistics Officer Nyongoro', 'Nyongoro', 'Operations', 'Occurrence book ', 'Major', '<p>Occurrence book is not filled with detailed accounts of occurrences.</p><p>The consistent report in the OB is on the buffalo disturbance and does not tell the compartments, the security guards who made observations and the actions taken.</p><p>Occurrences such as fire at Block 4 on 10th November and pastoralists camps in Block 7 in week 38 is not captured in the OB.&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2021-11-22', NULL, '2022-01-17', '2022-01-28', '2022-01-13', 'We have made a security plan and a form where security shall report every 30min from the start of their shift to the HOS who shal man the fixed radio station. This shall be by use of walkie talkies. The HOS/Ass shall record summary in the forms and detail occurences in the OB. Training shall be doen on the roll out of the walkie talkies and trainings expected to take place in January - KIA and Feb - NYO.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-11-18 08:22:08', '2022-03-29 12:10:21'),
(159, 16, 5, 3, 5, 3, NULL, '2021-11-18', '8876', 'Human resource manager', 'FOD & Quality Coordinator', 'Head Office', 'Operations', 'Nyongoro Security Vetting', 'Major', '<p>Most security guards are illiterate and can neither read nor write. (Security schedules and reports)&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2021-11-24', '2022-03-10', '2022-04-05', '2022-04-08', '2022-04-05', 'The Minimum grade was increased again from Class eight to Form four or KSCE Level.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-11-18 12:34:46', '2022-04-05 16:40:24'),
(160, 16, 5, NULL, 5, 3, NULL, '2021-11-18', '9776', 'Human resource manager', 'FOD & Quality Coordinator', 'Head Office', 'Operations', 'Nyongoro Security vetting', 'Major', '<p>Security personnel experience Clocking in challenges (Clock in late) especially when the Head of security is on leave</p>', 'closed', '2021-12-01', NULL, '2022-01-17', '2022-01-28', '2022-01-13', 'KIA: This has been rectified.\nNYO: We will have new HOS and Ass. HOS beginning of Feb. They will be trained again.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-11-18 12:36:41', '2022-03-01 14:30:59'),
(161, 16, 5, NULL, 23, 3, NULL, '2021-11-18', '69', 'Human resource manager', 'FOD & Quality Coordinator', 'Head Office', 'Operations', 'Nyongoro security vetting', 'Major', '<p>The squatters blame the BGF and not the county for eviction</p>', 'closed', '2021-11-24', NULL, '2021-11-25', '2021-11-26', '2021-11-24', 'We can only start working in areas where the ranch has solved THEIR problem. Our lease agreement says that the land shall be squatter free. Helping is one thing but being involved and having our equipment and staff put in danger is not acceptable.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-11-18 12:38:00', '2021-11-25 16:47:21'),
(162, 16, 5, NULL, 23, 19, NULL, '2021-11-18', '2467', 'Human resource manager', 'FOD & Quality Coordinator', 'Head Office', 'Operations', 'Nyongoro site visit', 'Major', '<p>PPEs (Overalls) that were worn out and needs to be discarded were still hanged.&nbsp;</p><p>CAR 9034: Raised to Human Resource Manager.</p>', 'closed', '2021-12-02', NULL, '2021-12-03', '2021-12-10', '2021-12-02', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-11-18 12:45:26', '2021-12-21 08:34:24'),
