(203, 19, 22, 29, 5, 19, NULL, '2022-02-01', '2735', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer Nyongoro', 'Site logistics Officer Nyongoro', 'Nyongoro', 'Operations', 'Work Instruction for filling IPR rev; 02/07/2014', 'Major', '<p>There was no Petrol in Nyongoro site from 24th January 2022 to 2nd February 2022.</p><p>According to Fuel records: Petrol ran out of stock on 21st January 2022.&nbsp;</p><p>SLM raised an IPR 1613 for 224litres of petrol on 21st January 2022, the same day it was depleted.</p><p>Staff have been buying fuel for use in supervision since 24th January. 1st February 2022, MEO and SFM plantations bought fuel.</p><p>Work instruction for raising IPR requires that items being requested for are put in order of priority. There are items that are &nbsp;needed immediately, in two or three weeks and soon.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2022-02-14', '2022-03-03', '2022-03-08', '2022-03-11', '2022-03-08', 'We have changed the issuance of stock procedure. Stock is first issued at Head office in sage before it is physically issued on site for all sites.', 'This is not at CAR!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! BE complete!', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-02-01 18:20:11', '2022-03-22 12:18:33'),
(204, 18, 13, 10, 8, 18, NULL, '2022-02-03', '2324', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks', 'Site Manager Farmers Programme 7Forks', '7 Forks', 'Forestry', '7 forks Forestry week 2 report and 7 forks Forestry week 5 plan.', 'Major', '<p>Six partner farmers that were corrected (Re-verified) by forestry in week 2 of 2022 had been scheduled to be corrected (Re-verified) again by forestry in the plan for week 5 of 2022. Repeat verification of the same farmers in the weekly forestry plan.&nbsp;</p><ul><li>In week 2: The 6 farmers were verified by Fredrick Ochieng&nbsp;</li><li>In week 5: 5 farmers were assigned to Anthony Ashiono and one re-assigned&nbsp;to Fredrick Ochieng.&nbsp;</li><li>The 6 farmers are from&nbsp;Kivou ward.&nbsp;</li><li>The weekly plan was prepared by SMFP&nbsp;</li></ul><p>1.<strong>Esther Gumba John</strong>&nbsp;</p><p>ID no:26180405.&nbsp;</p><p>Contract number: 17/ITB/001912.&nbsp;</p><p>2.<strong>Queen Elizabeth Mutisya</strong>.&nbsp;</p><p>ID no: 25181056.&nbsp;</p><p>Contract number:18/ITB/002403.&nbsp;</p><p>3.<strong>Joyce Syombua Mwendwa.</strong>&nbsp;</p><p>ID no: 12629131.&nbsp;</p><p>Contract number: 17/ITB/002183.&nbsp;</p><p>4.<strong>John Matei Mwanzia.</strong>&nbsp;</p><p>ID number: 13095740.&nbsp;</p><p>Contract number: 17/ITB/002044.&nbsp;</p><p>5.<strong> Gloria Kaluma Musyoka</strong>.&nbsp;</p><p>ID number: 8635231.&nbsp;</p><p>Contract number:17/ITB/001723.&nbsp;</p><p>6.<strong> Grace Nduni Kilonzo.</strong>&nbsp;</p><p>ID number: 776304&nbsp;</p><p>Contract number:17/ITB/001991.&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2022-02-04', '2022-03-03', '2022-03-15', '2022-12-31', '2022-03-10', 'Re-verification ended. This had to happen beacuase some farmers still did not have complete details to eneble us to upload their data in the back office. However this is a cost that must not be incurred again. Activities must be done right the first time. Managers on site must plan better, guide their teams appropriately, check frequently and react immediately when something is wrong. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-02-03 21:29:23', '2022-03-23 13:55:30'),
(205, 3, 22, 29, 5, 19, NULL, '2022-02-04', '3005', 'M&E Manager Kenya', 'Site logistics Officer Nyongoro', 'Nyongoro', 'Operations', 'Poor communication: Nyongoro site', 'Major', '<p>There was a communication gap observed between SLM Nyongoro and SFM Nursery Nyongoro after field visit by FOD, Ass. D-HR and OM in week 1,2022.</p><p>The Nyongoro Nursery was bushy and required weeding using Glyphosate by SFM Nursery.</p><p>The communication breakdown was observed where:</p><ul><li>1.The SLM was not aware that the nursery required water for Weed control.&nbsp;</li><li>2.The SFM said that he had communicated verbally to the SLM on the water required in the nursery.</li><li>3.SFM did not know why the nursery lacked water for weed control</li></ul><p>Emerging instances of poor communication are lack of communication on active CARs regarding nursery infrastructure from SLM to SFM and use of verbal communication in place of formal communication(Email).</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2022-02-14', '2022-03-03', '2022-03-08', '2022-03-11', '2022-03-08', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-02-04 17:47:39', '2022-03-11 18:41:23'),
(206, 3, 14, 9, 8, 19, NULL, '2022-02-04', '2493', 'M&E Manager Kenya', 'Site Manager Nursery Nyongoro', 'Nyongoro', 'Forestry', 'Poor communication: Nyongoro site', 'Major', '<p>There was a communication gap observed between SLM Nyongoro and SFM Nursery Nyongoro after field visit by FOD, Ass. D-HR and OM in week 1,2022.</p><p>The Nyongoro Nursery was bushy and required weeding using Glyphosate by SFM Nursery.</p><p>The communication breakdown was observed where:</p><ul><li>1.The SLM was not aware that the nursery required water for Weed control.&nbsp;</li><li>2.The SFM said that he had communicated verbally to the SLM on the water required in the nursery.</li><li>3.SFM did not know why the nursery lacked water for weed control</li></ul><p>Emerging instances of poor communication are lack of communication on active CARs regarding nursery infrastructure from SLM to SFM and use of verbal communication in place of formal communication(Email).</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2022-02-10', '2022-03-14', '2022-03-16', '2022-03-31', '2022-03-15', 'This is simply a case of poor planning. The site managers in forestry and operations have several meetings which provide platform to discuss and plan for activities but this is never done.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-02-04 17:47:39', '2022-03-22 12:14:32'),
(207, 19, 14, 9, 8, 19, NULL, '2022-02-05', '4295', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer Nyongoro', 'Site Manager Nursery Nyongoro', 'Nyongoro', 'Forestry', 'Nursery shade net frames', 'Major', 'Nursery shade net frames are weak and bent.', 'closed', '2022-02-10', '2022-03-14', '2022-03-16', '2022-03-31', '2022-03-15', 'The nursery will be repaired when production commences', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-02-06 00:16:28', '2022-03-17 12:55:55'),
(208, 19, 14, 9, 8, 19, NULL, '2022-02-06', '3363', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer Nyongoro', 'Site Manager Nursery Nyongoro', 'Nyongoro', 'Forestry', 'Hardening off tunnels', 'Major', '<p>16 tunnels haven\'t been repaired&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2022-02-10', '2022-02-28', '2022-03-16', '2022-03-31', '2022-03-15', 'Tunnels will be repaired when the production starts', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-02-06 12:15:58', '2022-03-17 12:55:22'),
(209, 2, 26, 8, 8, 2, NULL, '2022-02-11', '8874', 'Monitoring and Evaluation Officer Dokolo', 'Site Manager Farmers Program', 'Dokolo', 'Forestry', 'Farmer’s contract/agreement 2020: Obligations of the farmer; Clause10 : Farmer Shall not cut and or sell any trees before maturity without consulting BGF.', 'Major', '<p>A partner farmer cut down his Giant lira trees.&nbsp;</p><p>On 8th February 2022, &nbsp;MEO; Harriet Auma observed a farm (while on her way from verifying another farm) where 20 trees of Giant lira were being cut down in Agwata subcounty, Agwiciri parish, Alito village .</p><p>She was informed by the caretaker that the farm belongs to Bua Tonny (Not found in BGF Database) of Adeknino subcounty.</p><p>The reason for cutting the trees was that they were spoiling his crops although he didn’t elaborate how.&nbsp;</p><p>Harriet has encountered 2 more farms although the number of trees cut was less, 2 and 3 trees</p>', 'closed', '2022-02-14', '2022-05-25', '2022-05-27', '2022-06-03', '2022-05-25', 'ok', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-02-11 18:16:52', '2022-08-25 18:58:32'),
(210, 3, 15, 29, 5, 32, NULL, '2022-02-14', '1239', 'M&E Manager Kenya', 'Forest Technician Kiambere', 'Kiambere', 'Operations', 'Theft of site Items in Kiambere.', 'Major', '<p>Items stolen from Kiambere site stock.</p><p>On 31st January, HOS reported missing Items to FT.</p><p>FT took stock and confirmed that the following Items were missing. FT reported to the OM &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp; 1.Reflector jacket for Power saw operation (1 pc).</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;2.Riding gloves (a pair).&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;3.1 Pair of Pruning boots.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2022-04-07', '2022-04-26', '2022-06-21', '2022-07-31', '2022-06-15', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-02-14 17:45:54', '2022-07-26 17:25:27'),
(211, 16, 29, 29, 5, 3, NULL, '2022-02-14', '2688', 'Human resource manager', 'Operations Manager', 'Head Office', 'Operations', 'Staff performance evaluation', 'Major', '<ol><li>During the interaction with the Dokolo security team on Friday 4th February 2022 it came out that;</li><li>1. One security staff (Opio Paul) is illiterate and can neither read nor &nbsp;write&nbsp;</li><li>2. Sometimes security staff has to be reminded by the SLM &nbsp;to report to work and yet they have the approved schedules.</li><li>3. Late reporting to work by security staff.</li></ol>', 'closed', '2022-02-17', '2022-03-10', '2022-04-05', '2022-04-30', '2022-04-05', 'This is ok now', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-02-14 21:11:21', '2022-04-05 16:39:32'),
(212, 16, 29, 29, 5, 3, NULL, '2022-02-18', '8775', 'Deputy Director Human Resources', 'Operations Manager', 'Head Office', 'Operations', 'Daniel Exit Interview on 17thFebruary 2021', 'Major', '<p>Complaint on the repair of 7Forks motorbikes. When an IPR is raised it takes long before the motorbikes are repaired. This leads to the motorbikes having more issues at the time of repair.</p>', 'closed', '2022-02-21', '2022-03-03', '2022-03-31', '2022-08-01', '2022-03-08', 'What we need is a plan and the plan should be communicated on time with the supplier. The supplier should do inspection atleast 2 weeks to 3month period. Execution should be done within a week maximum.\nThe supplier should confirm availability at the time of quotation.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-02-18 20:09:23', '2022-03-16 15:52:19'),
(213, 16, 4, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-02-18', '7322', 'Deputy Director Human Resources', 'Deputy Director Communications', 'Head Office', 'Communications', 'Daniel Exit Interview on 17th February 2022', 'Major', '<p>No communication between Monitoring and Evaluation (GIC) staff and the technical committee to discuss any issues and suggestions. They are just given a calendar of activities at the beginning of the year and left to do things on their own.</p>', 'closed', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div>We will follow up regularly on GIC communications</div>', '<div>We will convey a meeting between the Kengen Foundation and BGF responsible to address this particular issue when SDF will be back from holiday (25th July)</div>', '', NULL, '2022-02-18 20:21:42', '2022-07-13 15:28:58'),
(214, 16, 5, 29, 5, 3, NULL, '2022-02-18', '9630', 'Deputy Director Human Resources', 'FOD & Quality Coordinator', 'Head Office', 'Operations', 'Daniel Exit interview on 17th February 2022', 'Major', '<p>Despite the good performance of the M&amp;E GIC, their salaries are frozen because of the MOU and this makes them demotivated.</p>', 'closed', '2022-02-25', '2022-03-03', '2022-04-05', '2022-04-08', '2022-04-05', 'This should solved through Forestry and HR', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-02-18 20:26:03', '2022-04-05 16:27:06'),
(215, 16, 16, 16, 23, 3, NULL, '2022-02-18', '6718', 'Deputy Director Human Resources', 'Deputy Director Human Resources', 'Head Office', 'HR', 'Daniel Exit interview on 17th February 2022', 'Major', '<p>Despite the good performance of the M&amp;E GIC, their salaries are frozen because of the MOU and this makes them demotivated.</p>', 'closed', '2022-03-11', '2022-03-17', '2022-04-28', '2022-05-05', '2022-04-28', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-02-18 20:26:04', '2022-07-14 18:53:39'),
(216, 18, 13, 10, 8, 18, NULL, '2022-02-21', '7240', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks', 'Site Manager Farmers Programme 7Forks', '7 Forks', 'Forestry', 'Outgrowers training Manual: version:200702 “BGF farmer  groups formation”', 'Minor', '<p><strong>As at 18/2/2022, 634 farmers out of 1,860 farmers who have planted are not in groups.&nbsp;</strong></p><p>The farmers who are not in groups are from all Wards of the 7 Forks programs.&nbsp;</p><p>The findings have been observed from the period June 2021 to February 2022.</p><p>The Farmer Group Coordination officer is responsible for the groups.&nbsp;</p><p>Analysis from the farmers comments showed that:</p><ul><li>98 farmers claimed that their existing groups are inactive</li><li>Some group are inactive example are Kinyambo and &nbsp;Nguka Mukau growers.</li><li>9 farmers claimed group conflicts</li><li>5 farmers claimed false promises by BGF</li><li>12 farmers intended to withdraw from the program</li></ul>', 'closed', '2022-02-25', '2022-03-03', '2022-03-16', '2022-06-30', '2022-03-15', 'The activity for past two years has been on inidvidual farme verification and not group formation. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-02-21 18:10:07', '2022-04-05 17:03:35'),
(217, 18, 13, 8, 8, 18, NULL, '2022-02-21', '528', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks', 'Site Manager Farmers Programme 7Forks', '7 Forks', 'Forestry', 'Out growers training Manual: version: 200702 ', 'Major', '<p><strong>As at 18/2/2022, 742 farmers out of 1,860 farmers who have planted do not have copy of their agreement</strong></p><p>The farmers spread throughout the wards of the 7 forks program</p><p>The findings have been observed from the period June 2021 to February 2022.&nbsp;</p><p>The site manager farmers program is responsible for the issuing of contracts.&nbsp;</p><p>Analysis from the farmers’ comments showed that:</p><ol><li>A partner misplaced his/her contract</li><li>Digitally contracted farmers have not been issued with contracts</li><li>A partner farmer has not been issued with a copy completely.</li></ol>', 'closed', '2022-02-28', '2022-05-25', '2022-05-27', '2022-12-31', '2022-05-25', 'ok', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-02-21 18:19:21', '2022-08-10 16:30:56'),
(218, 18, 13, 10, 8, 18, NULL, '2022-02-21', '622', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks', 'Site Manager Farmers Programme 7Forks', '7 Forks', 'Forestry', 'Forestry tree count verification report: June 2021 to February 2022.', 'Minor', '<p><strong>As at 18/2/2022, 51 farmers out of 1,860 farmers have incorrect Identification number.</strong></p><p>The farmers spread throughout the wards of the 7 forks program</p><p>The findings have been observed from the period June 2021 to February 2022.</p><p>The agro forestry agents are responsible for inputting correct Identification number.</p><p>Incorrect identification number are as result of:</p><ul><li>Inputting less or more digits e.g Patrick Kimwele Kilonzo correct(4880284) and incorrect( 4480248),Pius Munyasya correct(27722264) and incorrect (277222264).</li><li>Completely different identification numbers.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2022-02-25', '2022-03-03', '2022-03-16', '2022-06-30', '2022-03-15', 'Farmers program manager to use the attached list to correct the details of the farmers', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-02-21 18:29:28', '2022-08-10 16:31:58'),
(219, 18, 13, 10, 8, 18, NULL, '2022-02-21', '613', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks', 'Site Manager Farmers Programme 7Forks', '7 Forks', 'Forestry', ': Forestry tree count verification report: June 2021 to February 2022.', 'Minor', '<p><strong>As at 18/2/2022, 66 farmers out of 1,860 farmers have incorrect phone numbers.</strong></p><p>The farmers spread throughout the wards of the 7 forks program</p><p>The findings have been observed from the period June 2021 to February 2022.&nbsp;</p><p>The Agroforestry agents are responsible for recording correct phone numbers.</p>', 'closed', '2022-02-25', '2022-03-03', '2022-03-16', '2022-04-30', '2022-03-15', 'The farmers program manager to use attached list to correct farmer details. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-02-21 18:31:52', '2022-06-20 15:16:12'),
(220, 18, 13, 10, 8, 18, NULL, '2022-02-21', '2955', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks', 'Site Manager Farmers Programme 7Forks', '7 Forks', 'Forestry', 'Forestry tree count verification report: June 2021 to February 2022', 'Major', '<p><strong>As at 18/2/2022, 554 farmers out of 1,860 farmers have tree count variation.</strong></p><p>The farmers spread throughout the wards of the 7 forks program</p><p>The findings have been observed from the period June 2021 to February 2022.&nbsp;</p><p>The agro forestry agents are responsible for the counting of trees in the tree count verification.</p><p>Some reasons for tree count variation are; a partner farmer has &nbsp;planted his/her own trees and a representative is found during the visit and also mortality between Forestry count and M&amp;E count.</p>', 'closed', '2022-02-25', '2022-03-03', '2022-03-25', '2022-05-31', '2022-03-24', 'Decision shall be made by management on which figures to adopt. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-02-21 19:26:14', '2022-08-10 16:33:27'),
(221, 19, 22, 29, 5, 22, NULL, '2022-02-24', '8887', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer Nyongoro', 'Site logistics Manager Nyongoro', 'Nyongoro', 'Operations', 'Site clocking records and back end data', 'Major', '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Employee clocked in an activity that he didn’t do .</p><p>Employees should be assigned duties where they have been clocked&nbsp; in. &nbsp;</p><p>24/02/2022</p><p>2 permanent employees were clocked in 20622 NYO-Perm-Electric Fence-Maintenance. Walter was not present in the fence assessment process which was done by Wachira. &nbsp;This was noticed at I042 where M&amp;E only saw three individuals in timber sawing instead of four as was indicated in the record. Walter clocked in fence repair but was written as timber sawing. He was not present in either of the activities.</p><p>He was sent to collect fuel and other site supplies from Witu. He has also been assisting in the issuance of PPEs and tools both in the morning and in the evening since the year started.&nbsp;</p><p>In 2021 there was a CAR #210108-16 on the same non-conformance and was handled by creation of office administration task which he was clocking in but was later removed and replaced by house keeping task in which a temporary employee is clocked into.</p></td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', 'closed', '2022-03-04', '2022-03-10', '2022-04-05', '2022-04-30', '2022-04-05', 'We will get an SLO as communicated. However there is a some lack of planning and organization.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-02-25 01:01:42', '2022-07-26 17:29:31'),
(222, 18, 15, 29, 5, 32, NULL, '2022-03-06', '6107', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks', 'Forest Technician Kiambere', 'Kiambere', 'Operations', 'Site hygiene-No reference document.', 'Minor', '<p>The site bin was full of waste as a result of not burning the waste.Scattered pieces of logs were also observed inside &nbsp;and outside the nursery which is against site hygiene requirement.</p><p>This was observed on 2/03/2022.</p><p>Forest technician Kiambere is responsible for site hygiene.</p>', 'closed', '2022-03-25', '2022-04-26', '2022-06-21', '2022-07-31', '2022-06-15', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-03-06 23:47:51', '2022-07-26 17:34:32'),
(223, 16, 29, 3, 5, 3, NULL, '2022-03-09', '8196', 'Deputy Director Human Resources', 'Operations Manager', 'Head Office', 'Operations', 'Nyongoro SLM email request for staff allocation to do diesel pump operation', 'Major', '<p>There was no water for staff to wash hands at the pit latrines in week 8 as the handyman was on leave and there were no prior plans at the time of leave approval to have his essential duties to happen by somebody else.</p>', 'closed', '2022-03-10', '2022-03-10', '2022-04-05', '2022-04-08', '2022-04-05', 'The SLM is aware of what he supposed to do to get the required PMS. The rest is excuses and lack of planning.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-03-09 15:25:58', '2022-04-05 16:20:58'),
