(241, 32, 35, 8, 8, 3, NULL, '2022-03-18', '837', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks 2', 'Site Manager Farmers Programme 7Forks', '7 Forks', 'Forestry', 'Accounts records, week 7.', 'Major', '<p>M&amp;E verified that 1 partner farmer has a different Id number from what is in the accounts records.&nbsp;</p><p>The partner farmer is from kiomo Kyethani ward, mulatatunda village.</p><p>Verification was done in week 10 by M&amp;E from the data of week 7 accounts records.</p><p>The Id Number is wrongly recorded.&nbsp;</p><p>The AA responsible for this records is William Odede.</p><p>The list is in attached below.&nbsp;</p><p>Dorcas &nbsp;Mwende Mutambu Id provided is 36090154 &nbsp;phone number 0718450182.she confirmed that 0573919 is her correct Id Number.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2022-03-19', '2022-05-25', '2022-05-27', '2022-06-03', '2022-05-25', 'ok', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-03-18 04:32:42', '2022-05-27 18:58:19'),
(242, 34, 13, 13, 8, 2, NULL, '2022-03-21', '3754', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer Dokolo', 'Site Manager Dokolo site', 'Dokolo', 'Forestry', 'Accounts Farmer\'s database week 8', 'Major', '<p>Farmers without phone numbers</p><p>MEO Moses observed that 2 farmers did not have phone numbers during phone call verification.&nbsp;</p><p>The farmers were from the same subcounty (Amwoma) but different parishes and villages as seen below;</p><ol><li>1. Agweng Molly CF75074101QEWD -Apor village in Iguli Parish.</li></ol><p>2. Opio Tom CM86074103CQWG (Abandoned) - Amwoma village in Abucero parish.&nbsp;</p><p>This was observed in the M&amp;E week 11 plan and forestry week 8 report.</p><p>The information was submitted by AA Lameck Opito.</p>', 'closed', '2022-04-21', '2022-04-25', '2022-05-11', '2022-05-31', '2022-05-10', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-03-21 13:54:03', '2022-08-10 16:49:39'),
(243, 3, 35, 13, 8, 18, NULL, '2022-03-23', '9116', 'M&E Manager Kenya', 'Site Manager Farmers Programme 7Forks', '7 Forks', 'Forestry', '7 Forks records from Accounts department.', 'Major', '<p>Differences in the number of trees counted by Agroforestry Agents and M&amp;E Officers.</p><p>There were 143 farmers out of 246 who were found to have variances in the trees standing. This is 60% of those verified by farm visits. The variances range from 1 to 217 trees&nbsp;</p><p>The verification was from week 3 to week 11 of 2022.</p><p>The farmers are from 12 different wards monitored by 10 Agroforestry agents.</p><p>Attached list shows the farmers and their respective variances.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2022-03-28', '2022-04-25', '2022-05-11', '2022-12-31', '2022-05-10', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-03-23 16:14:47', '2022-08-25 18:59:21'),
(244, 2, 13, 13, 8, 2, NULL, '2022-03-23', '6065', 'Monitoring and Evaluation Officer Dokolo', 'Site Manager Dokolo site', 'Dokolo', 'Forestry', 'Farmers\' verification list from accounts', 'Minor', '<p>Wrong numbers recorded</p><p>While carryout farmer verification, MEO Diana encountered wrong numbers as elaborated below:</p><ol><li>1. Wrong number (0777387419) recorded for a partner farmer Apio Agnes of Amunamu village, Amunamu parish, Adok subcounty and Dokolo district</li></ol><p>The information is submitted in the forestry verification list of week 6 and week 10 of M&amp;E by Opito Lameck (AA)</p><ol><li>2. Ajuk Denish (CM86074102ND5L) of Akeogweno village, Western Ward parish, Dokolo Town Council subcounty, Dokolo District. The number recorded was for Pius Oladu (0786001589) who doesn’t know the farmer</li><li>&nbsp;</li><li>The information was submitted in the forestry verification list of week 8 and week 12 of M&amp;E by Ocen Bonny (AA)</li></ol><p>3. Omara Sam (CM69074102QHLE) of Akeogweno village, Western Ward parish, Dokolo Town Council subcounty, Dokolo District. The number recorded was for Henry Mutabazi (0775867758) who doesn’t know the farmer</p><p>The information was submitted in the forestry verification list of week 8 and week 12 of M&amp;E by Ocen Bonny (AA)</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2022-03-25', '2022-04-25', '2022-05-11', '2022-05-17', '2022-05-10', 'Reverification done by the site manager.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-03-23 20:09:55', '2022-05-11 13:50:07'),
(245, 19, 9, 9, 8, 19, NULL, '2022-03-23', '654', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer Nyongoro', 'Plantation Manager', 'Nyongoro', 'Forestry', 'Prospection activity', 'Major', '<p>The scope of prospection activity is not properly defined and is open for misuse by site managers.</p><p>The scope is unique depending on what the manager wants, it lacks unique checklists and work instructions.</p><p>PMS(Abdulla Salim) who was assigned prospection activity in G100 on 3rd March, 2022 counted trees that had been pruned. The pruned trees were those that were previously damaged by game. Report given to the SFM by the PMS was in terms of the number of trees that he counted in the compartments. The implementation by the PMS was in accordance with the instructions given by SFM.</p>', 'closed', '2022-04-14', '2022-04-19', '2022-04-19', '2022-04-29', '2022-04-19', 'The scope is defined in the checklist clearly stating the type of data to be recorded.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-03-24 02:45:25', '2022-04-30 11:29:37'),
(246, 2, 13, 13, 8, 2, NULL, '2022-03-24', '4237', 'Monitoring and Evaluation Officer Dokolo', 'Site Manager Dokolo site', 'Dokolo', 'Forestry', 'Farmer’s contract/agreement 2020: Obligations of the farmer; Clause10 : Farmer Shall not cut and or sell any trees before maturity without consulting BGF.', 'Major', '<p>10 Partner farmers cut down giant lira trees</p><p>During M&amp;E farmer verification, MEO Harriet encountered partner farmers who had cut down their giant lira trees in different villages (attached).</p><p>The reasons for cutting down trees were, they were flowering, fruiting and others were broken by wind and they decided to cut them completely.</p>', 'closed', '2022-03-25', '2022-04-25', '2022-05-11', '2022-08-31', '2022-05-10', NULL, '<div>To be closed.</div>', '<div>To be closed.</div>', '<div>To be closed.</div>', '<div>To be closed.</div>', '2022-03-24 12:34:35', '2023-02-22 16:20:50'),
(247, 2, 13, 13, 8, 2, NULL, '2022-03-24', '1929', 'Monitoring and Evaluation Officer Dokolo', 'Site Manager Dokolo site', 'Dokolo', 'Forestry', 'Farmer’s contract/agreement 2020: Obligations of the farmer; Clause10 : Farmer Shall not cut and or sell any trees before maturity without consulting BGF.', 'Major', '<p>A partner farmer is selling his 230 Giant lira trees</p><p>While MEO Diana was carrying out farmer verification in week 12 of M&amp;E and week 8 of forestry,&nbsp;</p><p>A farmer (Ogwany Lilly Aguti, 0783378823 NIN: CF75074103UVZH) of Akeogweno village, Western Ward parish, Dokolo Town Council, claimed to be waiting for the buyer who was going to pay for his trees on 24th March 2022</p><p>Reason for selling is, he got an accident in January, and he needs the money</p><p>The farmer was checked by AA, Ocen Bonny</p>', 'closed', '2022-03-25', '2022-04-25', '2022-05-11', '2022-05-31', '2022-05-10', NULL, '<div>To be closed.</div>', '<div>To be closed.</div>', '<div>To be closed.</div>', '<div>To be closed.</div>', '2022-03-24 18:01:55', '2023-02-22 16:20:12'),
(248, 2, 13, 13, 8, 2, NULL, '2022-03-25', '8189', 'Monitoring and Evaluation Officer Dokolo', 'Site Manager Dokolo site', 'Dokolo', 'Forestry', 'Farmers list from accounts', 'Minor', '<p>&nbsp;</p><p>Wrong numbers recorded</p><p>While carryout farmer verification, MEO Diana encountered wrong numbers as elaborated below:</p><p>1. Wrong number (0777387419) recorded for a partner farmer Apio Agnes of Amunamu village, Amunamu parish, Adok subcounty and Dokolo district</p><p>The information is submitted in the forestry verification list of week 6 and week 10 of M&amp;E by Opito Lameck (AA)</p><p>2. Ajuk Denish (CM86074102ND5L) of Akeogweno village, Western Ward parish, Dokolo Town Council subcounty, Dokolo District. The number recorded was for Pius Oladu (0786001589) who doesn’t know the farmer</p><p>The information was submitted in the forestry verification list of week 8 and week 12 of M&amp;E by Ocen Bonny (AA)</p><p>3. Omara Sam (CM69074102QHLE) of Akeogweno village, Western Ward parish, Dokolo Town Council subcounty, Dokolo District. The number recorded was for Henry Mutabazi (0775867758) who doesn’t know the farmer</p><p>The information was submitted in the forestry verification list of week 8 and week 12 of M&amp;E by Ocen Bonny (AA)</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2022-03-25', '2022-04-25', '2022-05-11', '2022-05-31', '2022-05-10', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-03-25 15:46:27', '2022-08-25 19:03:01'),
(249, 3, 13, 8, 8, 28, NULL, '2022-03-25', '2143', 'M&E Manager Kenya', 'Site Manager Dokolo site', 'Dokolo', 'Forestry', 'Dokolo records from Accounts department.', 'Major', '<p>Differences in the number of trees counted by Agroforestry Agents and M&amp;E Officers.</p><p>There were 213 farmers out of 336 who were found to have variances in the trees standing. This is 63% of those verified by farm visits. The variances range from 1 to 176 trees&nbsp;</p><p>The verification was from week 47 2021 to week 7 of 2022.</p><p>The farmers are from different sub counties monitored by different Agroforestry agents.(See list)</p><p>Attached list shows the farmers and their respective variances.</p>', 'closed', '2022-07-12', '2022-07-12', '2022-07-13', '2022-12-31', '2022-07-13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-03-25 18:39:15', '2022-08-25 19:03:31'),
(250, 34, 13, 13, 8, 2, NULL, '2022-03-26', '7959', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer Dokolo', 'Site Manager Dokolo site', 'Dokolo', 'Forestry', 'Accounts Farmers\' database', 'Major', '<p>Incorrect NIN number on the contract agreement</p><p>MEO Harriet during a farm visit observed that a farmer\'s NIN number on the hard copy contract agreement (contract number 799) was incorrectly written (see attached).</p><p>The farmer named AMONG SOFFIA is from Adok subcounty, Amunamun parish, Awidam village in Dokolo district.</p><p>The observation was made during a farm visit in the M&amp;E week 10 and Forestry verification report week 5, 2022.</p><p>The farmer\'s correct NIN number is CF5802210551QD.</p><p>The verification was by AA Ogole Pope Richard.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2022-04-21', '2022-04-25', '2022-05-11', '2022-06-30', '2022-05-10', 'Use the mobile app that allows to take picture of the NIN', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-03-26 11:15:24', '2022-08-25 19:04:07'),
(251, 34, 13, 13, 8, 2, NULL, '2022-03-26', '8715', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer Dokolo', 'Site Manager Dokolo site', 'Dokolo', 'Forestry', 'Accounts Farmers\' database', 'Major', '<p>Incorrect NIN numbers</p><p>MEO Harriet observed that 4 farmers\' NIN numbers were recorded incorrectly.</p><p>The farmers are from different locations in Dokolo district (see attached).</p><p>This was observed in different weeks of farm visits for forestry and M&amp;E (in the attached report).</p><p>The farm verification were by 2 different AAs (in the attached report).</p><p>3 of the NIN numbers are observed to be typing errors by the AA.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2022-04-21', '2022-04-25', '2022-05-11', '2022-06-30', '2022-05-10', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-03-26 11:47:13', '2022-08-25 19:04:54'),
(252, 32, 35, 35, 8, 18, NULL, '2022-03-26', '9188', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks 2', 'Site Manager Farmers Programme 7Forks', '7 Forks', 'Forestry', 'Ref:Account records;Week 8.', 'Minor', '<p>Incorrect phone numbers.&nbsp;</p><p>Two partner farmers verified by M&amp;E in week 11 from the data from week 8 of accounts.&nbsp;</p><p>The partner farmers were from mavuria ward, kiuriari and kambuki villages.&nbsp;</p><p>Phone number 0704159334 was copied from the database and 0712324466 does not belong to the farmer.&nbsp;</p><p>AA responsible for this record is John Njeru and Arshiphord kamau.</p><p>Here is the list of the two partner farmers.&nbsp;</p><p>1.Johnson Njeru Nderi Id 0941670 ,Incorrect phone number 0712324466,correct phone number 0112324466.</p><p>2.Elias Nyaga Ngari Id 21845317,Incorrect phone number 0704159334,correct phone number 0745929938.</p><p>1.Johnstone Njeru Nderi Id 0941670,Incorrect phone number 0712324466,correct phone number 0112324466.</p>', 'closed', '2022-03-27', '2022-04-25', '2022-05-11', '2022-05-31', '2022-05-10', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-03-27 02:58:16', '2022-05-14 15:01:41'),
(253, 23, 5, 29, 5, 3, NULL, '2022-03-26', '9123', 'Managing Director', 'FOD & Quality Coordinator', 'Head Office', 'Operations', 'Handling of damaged or obsolete goods', 'Major', '<p>More than 13 Million UGX of Miti Magazines written off in accounts without documentation, communication to relevant department head, authorisation and planning. Failure to initiate corrective action.&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2022-04-07', '2022-04-08', '2022-05-24', '2022-05-27', '2022-05-18', 'This is OK and approved.\na rack shall be purchased and the store shall be well arranged.\nMonthly stock is implelemented', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-03-27 03:07:37', '2022-07-26 17:37:51'),
(254, 32, 35, 35, 8, 18, NULL, '2022-03-27', '6880', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks 2', 'Site Manager Farmers Programme 7Forks', '7 Forks', 'Forestry', 'Ref:Accounts records;Week 8', 'Major', '<p>Partner farmers not in BGF mukau groups.&nbsp;</p><p>In week 11 from the data of week 8 accounts records M&amp;E verified that 6 Partner farmers were not in BGF mukau groups.&nbsp;</p><p>The partner farmers were from mavuria ward, Gitungati, kiuriari,Mathigira and kambuki villages&nbsp;</p><p>John Njeru and Arshiphord kamau are responsible for this record.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2022-03-27', '2022-04-25', '2022-05-11', '2022-11-01', '2022-05-10', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-03-27 04:17:16', '2022-05-14 14:14:03'),
