(260, 32, 35, 35, 8, 18, NULL, '2022-04-02', '3676', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks 2', 'Site Manager Farmers Programme 7Forks', '7 Forks', 'Forestry', 'Farmers database from accounts Week 8', 'Major', '<p>Wrong identification number.&nbsp;</p><p>A partner farmer who was verified in week 12 by M&amp;E &nbsp;had a &nbsp;different Id number 21536187 &nbsp;from what is in the farmers database accounts records &nbsp;31536187.</p><p>The partner farmer is from muminji ward, Ngurunga village.&nbsp;</p><p>The verification was done in week 12 by M&amp;E from data from week 8 of accounts records.&nbsp;</p><p>The difference is from typing errors.&nbsp;</p><p>The partner farmer\'s name, Boniface &nbsp;Njeru Kibindu Incorrect Id in account record is 31536187 and correct Id is 21536187,phone no 0711963603.</p><p>AA responsible is John Njeru.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2022-04-06', '2022-04-25', '2022-04-28', '2022-06-30', '2022-04-26', 'SFMFP to correct the ID in the database.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-04-02 04:38:33', '2022-05-07 13:49:39'),
(261, 32, 35, 35, 8, 18, NULL, '2022-04-02', '1106', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks 2', 'Site Manager Farmers Programme 7Forks', '7 Forks', 'Forestry', 'Farmers database from accounts Week 8', 'Major', '<p>Partner farmer who was not visited.&nbsp;</p><p>It was verified by M&amp;E in week 12 that a partner farmer from week 8 data of accounts records was not visited.&nbsp;</p><p>The partner farmer was from Muminji ward and Gitara village.&nbsp;</p><p>The partner farmer was visited lastly when John Njenga was an AA in her area.&nbsp;</p><p>The partner farmer is &nbsp;Dorothy Muthoni kithungi Id 28908297,phone is 0796356777.</p><p>AA responsible John Njeru.&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2022-04-06', '2022-04-25', '2022-05-11', '2022-05-13', '2022-05-10', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-04-02 04:55:23', '2022-08-25 19:13:50'),
(262, 32, 35, 35, 8, 18, NULL, '2022-04-02', '7977', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks 2', 'Site Manager Farmers Programme 7Forks', '7 Forks', 'Forestry', 'Farmers database from accounts, Week 4 and 8', 'Major', '<p>Partner farmers without hardcopy contracts.&nbsp;</p><p>M&amp;E verified in week 12 that 5 Partner farmers from the data of accounts records week 4 and 8 did not have hardcopy contracts.&nbsp;</p><p>The partner farmers were from Mavuria, Muminji and Kiambere wards, Ruthari, Kianjogu, Gitara and Rutumbi villages.&nbsp;</p><p>4 partner farmers have not been issued with hard copy contracts and one farmer was issued but during their domestic conflicts the copy of the contract was burnt with other personal belongings.&nbsp;</p><p>AAs responsible is John Njeru and Arshiphord kamau.&nbsp;</p><p>The list is in the attached evidence below.&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2022-04-06', '2022-04-25', '2022-05-11', '2022-12-31', '2022-05-10', '1. Reprint and issue farmers with contracts.\n2. train farmers on te importance of keeping the contracts safely', '<div>To be closed.</div>', '<div>To be closed.</div>', '<div>To be closed.</div>', '<div>To be closed.</div>', '2022-04-02 05:23:20', '2023-02-22 16:22:35'),
(263, 32, 35, 35, 8, 18, NULL, '2022-04-02', '1023', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks 2', 'Site Manager Farmers Programme 7Forks', '7 Forks', 'Forestry', 'Farmers database from accounts', 'Major', '<p>Partner farmers not in BGF mukau groups.&nbsp;</p><p>M&amp;E verified in week 12 from the data of week 8 of accounts records that &nbsp;4 Partner farmers were not in BGF mukau groups.&nbsp;</p><p>The partner farmers were from Mavuria, Evurore and Muminji wards, Ruthari,Kamigua,Ngurunga and Ciakaviu villages.&nbsp;</p><p>BGF mukau groups are inactive in farmers \' respective areas since the AAs were assigned to verifications.&nbsp;</p><p>AAs responsible is John Njeru and Arshiphord kamau.&nbsp;</p><p>The list below is the attached evidence.&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2022-04-06', '2022-04-25', '2022-05-11', '2022-11-30', '2022-05-10', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-04-02 05:40:47', '2022-05-14 13:52:28'),
(264, 19, 11, 9, 8, 19, 254, '2022-04-04', '4276', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer Nyongoro', 'Site Manager Plantation Nyongoro', 'Nyongoro', 'Forestry', 'Tree counting work instruction #210813', 'Major', '<p>Consistent underachievement of tree counting daily targets.</p><p>Tree counting task rates were not achieved by the two pms assigned the task throughout week 13. The daily targets for the two pms was 2400trees.&nbsp;</p><p>Daily task rate per Manday as indicated in the work instruction is 1200 trees.</p><p>The achievement was as follows.</p><p>28th March 2022 achieved &nbsp;520trees, 29th achieved 1160trees, 30th achieved 1571trees and 31st 875trees for compartments C081 on 28th March 2022, G033 on 29th 30th and 31st March 2022.</p><p>Pms who did tree counting were as follows.</p><p>28th and 29th; Elijah Njoroge and Omar Barisa.</p><p>30th and 31st; Elijah Njoroge and Ali Guyo.</p>', 'closed', '2022-05-03', '2022-05-05', '2022-05-11', '2022-05-31', '2022-05-10', 'Task rates are dynamic and change based on the area of work. This must be clearly indicated in the work instructions.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-04-04 11:58:52', '2022-08-25 19:15:50'),
(265, 34, 13, 13, 8, 2, NULL, '2022-04-10', '7665', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer Dokolo', 'Site Manager Dokolo site', 'Dokolo', 'Forestry', 'Accounts Farmer\'s Database', 'Major', '<p>1 Farmer was observed to be located in a different parish by MEO Moses during a farm visit in M&amp;E week 14.&nbsp;</p><p>The Farmer was verified &nbsp;by Agro-forestry Agent Opito Lameck in week 1 (2022).</p><p>The said farmer is called Ogwal Jaspher, contract number (1826), NIN (CM77074102ZUFK), Phone number (0775414700).</p><p>Accounts database location of the farmer is Adakogik B village, Alyecjuk Parish in Agwata subcounty, Dokolo district.&nbsp;</p><p>However, MEO observed the farmer to be located in Adakogik B, Agwiciri parish in Agwata Subcounty, Dokolo district.</p>', 'closed', '2022-04-21', '2022-04-25', '2022-05-11', '2022-06-30', '2022-05-10', NULL, '<div>To be closed.</div>', '<div>To be closed.</div>', '<div>To be closed.</div>', '<div>To be closed.</div>', '2022-04-10 20:46:55', '2023-02-22 16:23:06'),
(266, 18, 15, 10, 8, 18, NULL, '2022-04-11', '6046', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks', 'Forest Technician Kiambere', 'Kiambere', 'Forestry', 'Ms project plan for improved seedlings production at Kiambere Jan-Dec RV SN 220304,Methodology for setting up and execution of improved seedling production experiment.', 'Major', '<p>Transfer of 241 seedlings from traditional bed to Efford bed. Treatments E1 and E3 had no seedlings since the date of pricking out to 3/4/2022.From the results data sheet in one drive, treatments E1 &amp; E3 had 117 &amp; 124&nbsp; seedlings respectively as at 6/4/2022. Such an activity was not planned in work instruction and Ms Project plan for improved seedling seedlings production.</p><p>&nbsp;The M&amp;E observed this on data sheet filled by Forestry in one drive on 11/4/2022.</p><p>“I was instructed to move the seedlings in the quarterly meeting” FT comment.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;The FT Kiambere is responsible for implementation of the project’s activities.</p><p>&nbsp;Impact: The seedlings shall experience two different kinds of treatments in (Efford and Traditional) beds therefore skewing results of the experiment.</p>', 'closed', '2022-04-13', '2022-04-14', '2022-04-19', '2022-04-29', '2022-04-19', 'ok', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-04-11 17:23:05', '2022-05-20 16:14:46'),
(267, 34, 13, 13, 8, 2, NULL, '2022-04-19', '771', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer Dokolo', 'Site Manager Dokolo site', 'Dokolo', 'Forestry', 'Account\'s Farmers\' Database', 'Major', '<p>Incorrect NIN Numbers</p><p>MEO Harriet observed that 6 farmers\' NIN numbers were recorded incorrectly.</p><p>The farmers are from different locations in Dokolo district (see attached).</p><p>This was observed in different weeks of farm visits for forestry and M&amp;E (in the attached report).</p><p>The farm verifications were by 5 different AAs (in the attached report).</p><p>&nbsp;All of the NIN numbers are observed to be typing errors by the AAs.</p>', 'closed', '2022-04-21', '2022-04-25', '2022-05-09', '2022-05-31', '2022-05-09', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-04-19 14:38:06', '2022-08-25 19:18:24'),
(268, 32, 35, 35, 8, 32, NULL, '2022-04-19', '5118', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks 2', 'Site Manager Farmers Programme 7Forks', '7 Forks', 'Forestry', 'Farmers database accounts records week 45,46,47,48,49,50 and 51.', 'Major', '<p>Wrong phone numbers.&nbsp;</p><p>M&amp;E verified through a phone call that 9 partner farmers from farmers database accounts records have Wrong phone numbers.&nbsp;</p><p>The partner farmers were from Mumoni,Waita,Kiomo Kyethani and Kyuso wards-Kanyungu,Muliswa,kaleluni,Nzilani,Wikithuki,Musonoke,Kitulu,Kamathiitu Central and kwambolo villages.&nbsp;</p><p>The verification was done in week 14 and 15 by M&amp;E from the data from week 45,46,47,48,50 and 51 of farmers accounts records.&nbsp;</p><p>The farmers phone numbers from farmers database accounts records was contacted by M&amp;E and &nbsp;the persons who answered the calls were from Nakuru, Meru,Rongai,Eldoret and kibera and have no clue about farmers program in 7Forks .</p><p>The responsible AAs were Fredrick Ochieng,Odede,Liyayi,Anthony and Nancy Auma.</p><p>The attached is the list of evidence.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2022-04-22', '2022-04-25', '2022-05-09', '2022-05-31', '2022-05-09', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-04-19 14:42:20', '2022-06-18 00:10:04'),
(269, 34, 13, 13, 8, 2, NULL, '2022-04-19', '1785', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer Dokolo', 'Site Manager Dokolo site', 'Dokolo', 'Forestry', 'Accounts Farmers\' Database', 'Major', '<p>Incorrect Farmer\'s location (District)</p><p>1 farmer was observed to be in a diferent district by MEO Moses during a farm visit in week 15.</p><p>The said farmer is called Atim Margret, contract number (UG00632), NIN ( CF63001101TRAJ).</p><p>The farmer was verified by Agro-forestry agent Ocen Bonny Bob in week 2.</p><p>Accounts farmers\' database records show farmer to be located in Dokolo district, Adok subcounty, Amunamun parish, Tetol village.</p><p>MEO\'s observation: Farmer is located in Apach district, Kwania county, Abongomola subcounty, Agwa parish, Amuda A village.</p>', 'closed', '2022-04-21', '2022-04-25', '2022-05-09', '2022-06-01', '2022-05-09', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-04-19 15:01:06', '2022-08-25 19:20:06'),
(270, 34, 13, 13, 8, 2, NULL, '2022-04-19', '7790', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer Dokolo', 'Site Manager Dokolo site', 'Dokolo', 'Forestry', 'Accounts Farmers\' Database', 'Major', '<p>Incorrect subcounty, parish</p><p>1 farmer was observed to be located in a different subcounty and parish by MEO Moses during a farm visit in week 7.</p><p>The farmer is called Elel Isaac, NIN (CM93074102ZJMA), contract number (1843).</p><p>Accounts farmers\' database says the farmer is located in Amwoma subcounty, Amwoma Parish, Alito village in Dokolo district.</p><p>MEO observation: Farmer is located in Agwata subcounty, Agwiciri parish, Alito village, Dokolo district.</p><p>The farmer was verified by Agroforestry Agent, Akullu Harriet in week 3.</p>', 'closed', '2022-04-21', '2022-04-25', '2022-05-09', '2022-05-31', '2022-05-09', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-04-19 15:19:22', '2022-08-25 19:21:15'),
