(376, 16, 4, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-06', '3636', 'Deputy Director Human Resources', 'Deputy Director Communications', 'Head Office', 'Communications', 'Forestry(manual cleaning)task allocation to two tractor drivers(Nyongoro Site)', 'Major', '<ol><li>1. Two tractor drivers(Operations dept)were assigned manual cleaning(Forestry dept) and this was not explained to them by neither the SLM nor the SMP. They were just told by the SMP to go to the store and pick up the pangas and proceed to work. They refused to clock in and only did so after DDHR intervened and explained to them.</li><li>&nbsp;</li></ol>', 'closed', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '<div>This particular occurrence was addressed by DDHR.<br>DDC addressed the issue in the Forestry and Operations communications meeting and will continuously address similar occurrences at the individual levels in coordination with DDHR.</div>', '', NULL, '2022-06-06 20:23:32', '2022-07-13 15:34:21'),
(377, 19, 22, 29, 5, 19, NULL, '2022-06-06', '6498', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer Nyongoro', 'Site logistics Manager Nyongoro', 'Nyongoro', 'Operations', 'Task allocation to employees', 'Major', '<p>Two employees deliberately refused to be clocked in for tasks</p><p>Hassan Galgalo and Godana Hamisi refused to be clocked in for manual cleaning tasks on 6th June 2022.</p><p>They claimed to have been employed as drivers hence being assigned manual cleaning task was not in order. SFM and SLM informed the two on the task changes on 4th June.</p><p>Hassan Galgalo was not clocked in completely on 6th while Godana reconsidered to clock in which he did at 11.16am after which he was taken through work instruction and started work at 12.30pm. He achieved 0.02ha. He worked in the moringa field contrary to where he had clocked in-E025.</p>', 'closed', '2022-06-15', '2022-06-15', '2022-07-13', '2022-07-31', '2022-07-13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-07 00:08:14', '2022-07-27 15:40:43'),
(378, 32, 15, 29, 5, 32, NULL, '2022-06-08', '7750', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks 2', 'Forest Technician Kiambere', 'Kiambere', 'Operations', 'Site infrastructure-no reference document', 'Minor', '<p>Locks not locking the gentlemen latrine doors.</p><p>The M&amp;E observed that the gentlemen latrine doors locks could not close from outside.</p><p>This was seen in kiambere site in week 23 by M&amp;E .</p><p>The locks was wrongly fixed since the positioning of the sliding bolt does not fit into the latch bore hence the gentlemen latrine doors could not be closed from outside.</p><p>FT is responsible for this record.</p><p>Below is attached evidence.</p>', 'closed', '2022-06-10', '2022-06-15', '2022-07-13', '2022-07-31', '2022-07-13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-09 02:55:02', '2022-07-27 15:39:43'),
(379, 16, 4, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-09', '2677', 'Deputy Director Human Resources', 'Deputy Director Communications', 'Head Office', 'Communications', 'Dokolo security absence(2nd to 4th June) ', 'Major', '<p>One security guard in the Dokolo site(Ogwal Moses) was absent from work from 2nd to 4th June and there was no communication with the head office. The SLM sent an email communication on 6th June. The other guards had to work overtime to cover for him.</p>', 'closed', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '<div>This particular occurrence was addressed by DDHR.<br>DDC addressed the issue in the Forestry and Operations communications meeting and will continuously address similar occurrences at the individual levels in coordination with DDHR.</div>', '', NULL, '2022-06-09 16:13:16', '2022-07-13 15:34:41'),
(380, 32, 15, 10, 8, 32, NULL, '2022-06-10', '7109', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks 2', 'Forest Technician Kiambere', 'Kiambere', 'Forestry', 'Improved seedling production Trial 2022 - Root measurement Methodology.', 'Minor', '<p>Un appropriate materials used in root measurement.</p><p>Root measurement methodology materials are:Razor blade,Calibrated glass and pieces of old newspaper.A syringe and part of polythene sheet was used.</p><p>This was observed in kiambere by M&amp;E in week 23.</p><p>The root measurement is obtained by quantifying the volume of liquid a root displaced when submerged inside a vessel of water.A syringe was too small for root measurement and therefore no measurement was done.</p><p>FT is responsible.</p><p>The attach is the evidence.</p>', 'closed', '2022-06-15', '2022-06-16', '2022-07-04', '2022-08-04', '2022-07-03', 'This is ok. The idea was to get the correct volume of the roots.', '<div>To be closed.</div>', '<div>To be closed.</div>', '<div>To be closed.</div>', '<div>To be closed.</div>', '2022-06-10 21:21:59', '2023-02-22 16:53:38'),
(381, 17, 4, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-15', '8016', 'Systems & Administration Manager', 'Deputy Director Communications', 'Head Office', 'Communications', 'TICKETING SYSTEM FEEDBACK', 'Minor', '<p>We have noted with great concern that, once we respond to the tickets initiated, &nbsp;the admin expects to get feedback from the initiator but currently not happening hence slowing the process of communication on feedback.&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '<div>This has been addressed through email from S.A.M to all staff. To follow up to measure the effectiveness this week(Week 27).</div>', '<h1><br></h1>', NULL, '2022-06-15 18:54:44', '2022-07-13 15:34:58'),
(382, 16, 4, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-16', '8487', 'Deputy Director Human Resources', 'Deputy Director Communications', 'Head Office', 'Communications', 'Email by SMD to the HOD  on lack of  communication by 3 Dokolo staff who are absent', 'Major', '<p>Against the policy, three staff(AAs) from the Dokolo site did not report to work and they did not inform their supervisor.This affects the forestry plans and tasks.</p>', 'closed', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '<div>This particular occurrence was addressed by DDHR and DDC week 25.<br>DDC will continuously address similar occurrences at the individual levels in coordination with DDHR.</div>', '', NULL, '2022-06-16 19:15:33', '2022-07-13 15:35:20'),
(383, 32, 15, 29, 5, 32, NULL, '2022-06-18', '2861', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks 2', 'Forest Technician Kiambere', 'Kiambere', 'Operations', 'Preventive Maintainance', 'Major', '<p>M&amp;E observed that the schedule plan of week 24 in kiambere site operations,fencing was suppose to be done on 13/6/22 on compartment A007 by 2 PMS.</p><p>This was observed on 13/6/22 that fencing was not done on compartment A007 in kiambere site as per the plan.</p><p>FT is responsible.</p>', 'closed', '2022-06-22', '2022-06-28', '2022-07-13', '2022-07-31', '2022-07-13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-18 17:59:53', '2022-07-28 17:47:48'),
(384, 32, 15, 9, 8, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-18', '6949', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks 2', 'Forest Technician Kiambere', 'Kiambere', 'Forestry', 'Plantation management.', 'Major', '<p>M&amp;E noticed that in week 24 kiambere site forestry plan,manual cleaning was schedule to be done on 13/6/22 in compartment A044 by 2 PMS but the activity was carried out in compartment A043.</p><p>This was observed &nbsp;on 13/6/22 &nbsp;in kiambere site compartment A043 by M&amp;E.The PMS were in full PPE cleaning with pangas.</p><p>FT said ‘’ The two compartments bounder each other and both &nbsp;of them needs the same treatment\".</p><p>FT is responsible.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2022-07-15', '2022-07-18', NULL, NULL, '2022-07-03', 'We need facts to make a decision that will prevent this from recurring. The Ft and the planations manager need to provide this. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-18 18:35:36', '2023-02-22 16:24:46'),
(385, 32, 35, 29, 5, 32, NULL, '2022-06-18', '1901', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks 2', 'Site Manager Farmers Programme 7Forks', '7 Forks', 'Operations', 'Health and safety -House keeping.', 'Minor', '<p>Tables not cleaned and disinfected twice a day.</p><p>The house keeping checklist a phrase states that ‘ clean and disinfect surfaces which are extensively used twice a day like tables’. In 7Forks cleaning of tables is done once in the morning hours only and there\'s no disinfection done at all.</p><p>This was observed on 16/6/22 in 7F (office).</p><p>The house keeper does cleaning only in the morning hours signs work done and leaves .</p><p>Site manager 7Forks is responsible.</p>', 'closed', '2022-06-21', '2022-06-28', '2022-07-13', '2022-07-31', '2022-07-13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-18 19:02:50', '2023-01-25 16:09:36'),
(386, 32, 15, 29, 5, 32, NULL, '2022-06-18', '626', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks 2', 'Forest Technician Kiambere', 'Kiambere', 'Operations', 'Communication - No written document.', 'Minor', '<p>Weekly plan not pinned on the notice board.</p><p>In week 24 kiambere site weekly plan was suppose to be pinned on the notice board but the weekly plan was not pinned on the notice board.</p><p>This was observed by M&amp;E on 13/6/22 at kiambere site.</p><p>M&amp;E visited kiambere site on 13/6/22 and wanted to confirm whether kiambere site weekly planwas amended or not but there was no pinned plan on the notice board.</p><p>FT is responsible.</p>', 'closed', '2022-06-21', '2022-06-28', '2022-07-13', '2022-07-31', '2022-07-13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-19 03:58:57', '2022-07-28 18:14:16'),
(387, 19, 22, 29, 5, 19, NULL, '2022-06-19', '8175', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer Nyongoro', 'Site logistics Manager Nyongoro', 'Nyongoro', 'Operations', 'Tents', 'Major', '<p>Two out of the three tents at the site have faulty zips</p><p>The two tents can not be zipped due to faulty zips. This resulted to one donkey entering the tents and consuming food staffs that were suspected to have contributed to the death of the donkey on 25th May 2022.</p><p>Unzipped tent can also allow crawing insects/animals with are irritating or harmful entering the tents.</p>', 'closed', '2022-06-28', '2022-06-28', '2022-07-13', '2022-07-31', '2022-07-13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-19 13:59:16', '2022-07-28 18:54:03'),
(388, 19, 22, 29, 5, 19, NULL, '2022-06-19', '6513', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer Nyongoro', 'Site logistics Manager Nyongoro', 'Nyongoro', 'Operations', 'Preventive maintenance for Diesel water pump', 'Major', '<p>Diesel water pump is leaking oil.</p><p>The &nbsp;leaking is due to worn out oil seals. This could not be promptly fixed-The mechanic was on sick leave from 14th to 18th June. Week 24.</p>', 'closed', '2022-06-28', '2022-06-28', '2022-07-13', '2022-07-31', '2022-07-13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-19 14:26:58', '2022-07-28 18:31:27'),
(389, 32, 15, 9, 8, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-19', '2427', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks 2', 'Forest Technician Kiambere', 'Kiambere', 'Forestry', 'Plantation management', 'Major', '<p>Pruning was not done in compartment A044.</p><p>Week 24 kiambere site forestry plan,manual pruning was schedule to be done in compartment A044 on 13/6/22 by &nbsp;2 PMS but the activity (manual pruning) was carrid out in compartment A040.</p><p>M&amp;E observed this in kiambere site on 13/6/22.</p><p>M&amp;E found two PMS in full PPE doing pruning by use of long handled pruning saws.</p><p>FT is responsible .</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2022-07-15', '2022-07-18', NULL, NULL, '2022-07-03', 'The FT and the manager of the plantation have not given a satisfactory explanation for this. We need a clearer view of what happened or why that was the case to find a lasting solution.', '<div>To be closed.</div>', '<div>To be closed.</div>', '<div>To be closed.</div>', '<div>To be closed.</div>', '2022-06-19 14:32:04', '2023-02-22 16:53:04'),
(390, 32, 15, 29, 5, 32, NULL, '2022-06-19', '5819', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks 2', 'Forest Technician Kiambere', 'Kiambere', 'Operations', 'Healthy and safety -House keeping.', 'Minor', '<p>There was no sanitizers at agreed points.</p><p>M&amp;E realised that in kiambere site, there was only hand washing soap at washing agreed points.Hand sanitizers were not placed at washing points on 13/6/22.</p><p>FT is responsible.</p><p>Attached is the evidence.</p>', 'closed', '2022-06-21', '2022-07-04', '2022-07-13', '2022-07-14', '2022-07-13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-19 15:05:43', '2022-07-28 18:33:28'),
(391, 32, 15, 29, 5, 32, NULL, '2022-06-19', '7154', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks 2', 'Forest Technician Kiambere', 'Kiambere', 'Operations', 'Security occurance book', 'Minor', '<p>Daily occurance booked in occurance &nbsp;book and not signed.</p><p>M&amp;E observed on 13/6/22 week 24 that daily occurance No.024,025,026,033 and 034 were booked but not signed.After every booked occurance it must be signed by the head of security.</p><p>This was observed in kiambere site on 13/6/22.</p><p>Some occurance reported are booked and not signed.</p><p>FT is responsible.</p><p>Attached is the evidence.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2022-06-21', '2022-06-28', '2022-07-13', '2022-07-22', '2022-07-13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-19 16:55:32', '2022-07-28 18:52:39'),
(392, 32, 15, 9, 8, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-19', '5466', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks 2', 'Forest Technician Kiambere', 'Kiambere', 'Forestry', 'Plantation management.', 'Major', '<p>Tree counting not achieved.</p><p>M&amp;E observed &nbsp;kiambere site forestry plan in week 24 that tree counting task rate is 1200 per PMS.Tree counting was carried out in compartment A009 by 2 PMS who had a target of 2400 trees .The 2 PMS under achieved &nbsp;by counting 1994 trees in compartment A009.</p><p>This was observed on 13/6/22 in kiambere site by M&amp;E.</p><p>FT is responsible.</p><p>Attached is the evidence record.</p>', 'closed', '2022-07-15', '2022-07-18', NULL, NULL, '2022-07-03', 'The explanation by the FT and the Manager for the significant reduction in task rates is not satisfactory. They must state exactly what caused the reduction. Decisions to change task rates must be based on facts. ', '<div>To be closed.</div>', '<div>To be closed.</div>', '<div>To be closed.</div>', '<div>To be closed.</div>', '2022-06-19 17:23:16', '2023-02-22 16:27:38'),
(393, 32, 35, 8, 8, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-19', '9697', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks 2', 'Site Manager Farmers Programme 7Forks', '7 Forks', 'Forestry', 'Group sensitation and capacity buliding report week 23.', 'Minor', '<p>There was one blank space whereby the ward name of a contracted farmer was not indicated.</p><p>The names, Identification numbers and the identification photos for two representatives were recorded instead of contracted farmers.</p><p>Four(4) contracted farmers shared the same phone numbers.</p><p>The ttached evidence contain the list of the contracted farmers with specific non conformance.</p><p>The M&amp;E did verification of the report in week 24.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2022-07-15', '2022-08-08', NULL, NULL, '2022-07-03', 'It is not clear what the non-conformance is here.', '<div>To be closed.</div>', '<div>To be closed.</div>', '<div>To be closed.</div>', '<div>To be closed.</div>', '2022-06-19 18:01:30', '2023-02-22 16:52:30'),
(394, 19, 11, 9, 8, 19, NULL, '2022-06-20', '8455', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer Nyongoro', 'Site Manager Plantation Nyongoro', 'Nyongoro', 'Forestry', 'Handling of logs extracted from the plantation.', 'Major', '<p>Extracted logs have been placed in the open exposing them to rain and sun.</p><p>8 logs that were brought to site on 17th May are still in the open. There exposure to the external and various weather conditions will lead to deterioration of their wood quality.</p>', 'closed', '2022-06-27', '2022-06-29', '2022-07-04', '2022-08-31', '2022-07-03', 'This is an activity executed by operations.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-20 14:49:02', '2022-07-18 22:36:56'),
(396, 23, 8, 8, 8, 18, NULL, '2022-06-21', '6374', 'Managing Director', 'Executive Director Forestry', 'Head Office', 'Forestry', 'GIC work', 'Major', '<p>Dear all.</p><p>I hope this finds you well, i am writing to the subject highlighted in relation to the meal and accommodation allowance for the Months of May and June 2022. Despite making the work plan and cash request on time and sending them to the relevant supervisors, there has been no clear communication on the payment of allowance. the activities for the month of May were done and reports send to relevant department they included, GIC VII launch preparation, the Launch ceremony, GIC VII monitoring Kitui County and GIC IV Second runners up trip. for the month of June GIC VII monitoring for the machakos County Has been conducted and&nbsp; 8 schools in Embu. All these times our immediate supervisor SMFP has been telling us to execute the field work with our money since the Cash requests were still in process. We hereby seek guidance on the way forward and how to undertake the field activities without facilitation since the cash processing has taken too long.</p>', 'closed', '2022-07-12', '2022-07-12', '2022-07-13', '2022-07-31', '2022-07-13', NULL, '<div>!. The planning for the GIC program is poor.<br><br>The team especially the monitoring and evaluation officers shall be obliged like the rest of the BGF programs to make both yearly and monthly plans well in advance for approval and use to run the program.&nbsp;<br><br>The program manager got a warning letter for letting the officers use their own money without approval.&nbsp;</div>', '<div>To be closed.</div>', '<div>To be closed.</div>', '<div>To be closed.</div>', '2022-06-21 14:14:10', '2023-02-22 16:47:27'),
