(437, 36, 4, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-30', '72752', 'FSC Officer', 'Communications Department', 'Head Office', 'Communications', 'Interim National Standard.\" The organization shall have a management plan consistent with its policies and objectives and proportionate to scale intensity and risks of its management activities.\" (principle 7)', 'Major', '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>FSC GAPS RELATED TO MANAGEMENT PLAN</strong></td><td><strong>A.O</strong></td></tr><tr><td><ol><li>1. There is no management plan in place.</li></ol></td><td>Forestry</td></tr><tr><td>2. There is no records/list of communities around the MU affected by management activities.</td><td>Forestry</td></tr><tr><td>3. No insect pest management system in place.</td><td>Forestry</td></tr><tr><td>4. There is no records of High Conservation Values found in the management unit.</td><td>Forestry</td></tr><tr><td>5. No management unit history records/forms.</td><td>Forestry</td></tr><tr><td>6. There is no identified representative sample set aside for conservation.</td><td>Forestry</td></tr><tr><td>7. No records of Rare threatened and endangered species identified in the MU.</td><td>Forestry</td></tr><tr><td>8. Documented records of community engagement process and their rights.</td><td>Forestry</td></tr><tr><td>9. No harvesting/ regeneration plan and harvesting procedures put in place.</td><td>Forestry</td></tr><tr><td>10. No procedure for infrastructure development and maintenance.</td><td>Operations</td></tr><tr><td>11. No records of natural hazard assessment and their mitigation measures.</td><td>Forestry/operations</td></tr><tr><td>12. No chemical use procedure.</td><td>Forestry</td></tr><tr><td>13. No records of resources and ecosystem services in the management unit.</td><td>Forestry</td></tr><tr><td>14. No waste management records and procedure.</td><td>Operations</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2022-07-06', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '<div>No direct interventions of communications are needed at this point.<br><br></div>', '', NULL, '2022-06-30 21:06:09', '2022-07-13 15:37:54'),
(438, 36, 8, 8, 8, 18, NULL, '2022-06-30', '6112', 'FSC Officer', 'Executive Director Forestry', 'Head Office', 'Forestry', 'Interim National Standard.\" The organization shall have a management plan consistent with its policies and objectives and proportionate to scale intensity and risks of its management activities.\" (principle 7)', 'Major', '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>FSC GAPS RELATED TO MANAGEMENT PLAN</strong></td><td><strong>A.O</strong></td></tr><tr><td><ol><li>1. There is no management plan in place.</li></ol></td><td>Forestry</td></tr><tr><td>2. There is no records/list of communities around the MU affected by management activities.</td><td>Forestry</td></tr><tr><td>3. No insect pest management system in place.</td><td>Forestry</td></tr><tr><td>4. There is no records of High Conservation Values found in the management unit.</td><td>Forestry</td></tr><tr><td>5. No management unit history records/forms.</td><td>Forestry</td></tr><tr><td>6. There is no identified representative sample set aside for conservation.</td><td>Forestry</td></tr><tr><td>7. No records of Rare threatened and endangered species identified in the MU.</td><td>Forestry</td></tr><tr><td>8. Documented records of community engagement process and their rights.</td><td>Forestry</td></tr><tr><td>9. No harvesting/ regeneration plan and harvesting procedures put in place.</td><td>Forestry</td></tr><tr><td>10. No procedure for infrastructure development and maintenance.</td><td>Operations</td></tr><tr><td>11. No records of natural hazard assessment and their mitigation measures.</td><td>Forestry/operations</td></tr><tr><td>12. No chemical use procedure.</td><td>Forestry</td></tr><tr><td>13. No records of resources and ecosystem services in the management unit.</td><td>Forestry</td></tr><tr><td>14. No waste management records and procedure.</td><td>Operations</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2022-07-06', '2022-07-06', '2022-07-07', '2022-07-31', '2022-07-06', 'This CAR will be closed and individual non-conformances addressed by respective departments.', '<div>To be closed.</div>', '<div>To be closed.</div>', '<div>To be closed.</div>', '<div>the CARs were raised separately&nbsp;</div>', '2022-06-30 21:06:09', '2023-02-22 16:38:56'),
(439, 32, 15, 29, 5, NULL, NULL, '2022-07-05', '2137', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks 2', 'Forest Technician Kiambere', 'Kiambere', 'Operations', 'PPE Management policy', 'Major', '<p>One PMS did not wear gloves.</p><p>On 5/7/22 during manual cleaning in compartment A036,it was observed that an employee who was spraying the shrubs stumps by use of glyphosate had not worn gloves.</p><p>The worker was asked why he did not wear gloves and he answered ‘’i just forgot\".</p><p>The purpose of wearing PPE is to reduce employee exposure to health hazards when at work.</p><p>This was observed by M&amp;E in week 27 at kiambere site.</p><p>FT is responsible to ensure that employees wear the protective gears at work.</p><p>Below is the attached evidence.</p>', 'closed', '2022-07-15', '2022-07-18', NULL, NULL, '2022-07-13', 'is clocking out a worker who fails to wear PPE in HR or H&S policy?', '', '<div>FT should continue hammering the importance of wearing the complete set of PPEs. This will be monitored on the Health and Safety site meeting minutes. FT to be conducting spot checks to ensure all workers wear complete PPE set</div>', '<div>CAR is not complete it does not state the details of the worker and there was no evidence attached as stated above.<br>It is the work of the FT to make certain that all staff have their respective PPES and it\'s his duty to check regularly and ensure all workers comply with the policy.</div>', NULL, '2022-07-06 03:53:47', '2022-09-15 15:03:31'),
(440, 32, 15, 29, 5, 32, NULL, '2022-07-05', '2430', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks 2', 'Forest Technician Kiambere', 'Kiambere', 'Operations', 'Drinking water tank-No reference document.', 'Major', '<p>Leaking water tank.</p><p>There was leaking water from the outlet fittings and the tap connecting the water tank.</p><p>A water storage tank should not be leaking to avoid waste of company\'s resources.</p><p>This was observed by M&amp;E in week27 at kiambere site.</p><p>FT is responsible to make sure that there is no leaking water tank in kiambere site.</p><p>Below ia attached leaking points of drinking water tank.</p>', 'closed', '2022-07-08', '2022-07-08', '2022-07-19', '2022-07-31', '2022-07-13', NULL, '<div>The repair shall be done immediately before we start buying drinking water.<br>This is to be done when the water currently in the tank is finished.<br>The Filters funnel should be fixed and the tap where workers collect water fixed separately on wall. The area of the tank with the filters should be enclosed.<br>We need to investigate the filtration system and find out what we are not doing right.</div>', '<div>This should be on preventive maintenance and frequently assessed.&nbsp;</div>', '<div>The drinking water tank should be under preventive maintenance to ensure everything is in order at all times.</div>', NULL, '2022-07-06 04:08:09', '2022-11-22 20:17:36'),
(441, 4, 5, 29, 5, 18, NULL, '2022-07-06', '4508', 'Deputy Director Communications', 'FOD & Quality Coordinator', 'Head Office', 'Operations', 'Weekly follow-up on CARs', 'Major', '<p>Auditees do not respond or respond late to CARs despite being notified via mail on new CAR\'s</p>', 'closed', '2022-07-14', '2022-07-15', '2022-07-20', '2022-07-31', '2022-07-20', NULL, '', '<div>We will keep monitoring.</div>', '<div>Okay.</div>', NULL, '2022-07-06 15:05:12', '2022-09-15 15:14:01'),
(442, 19, 22, 29, 5, 19, NULL, '2022-07-07', '1101', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer Nyongoro', 'Site logistics Manager Nyongoro', 'Nyongoro', 'Operations', 'Handling of logs extracted from the plantation.', 'Major', '<p>Extracted logs have been placed in the open exposing them to rain and sun.</p><p>8 logs that were brought to site on 17th May are still in the open. There exposure to the external and various weather conditions will lead to deterioration of their wood quality.</p>', 'closed', '2022-07-12', '2022-07-12', '2022-07-14', '2022-10-01', '2022-07-13', NULL, '<div>We need to construct a raised platform for the logs with a support on sites with a makuti roof.<br>Put all the fallen trees in one place (nursery) and we make a simple platform.<br>By 31.11.2022, a submit a plan and IPR</div>', '<div>The above is operational.</div>', '<div>To be addressed by operations department</div>', NULL, '2022-07-07 16:06:06', '2022-11-22 20:28:09'),
(447, 16, 8, 8, 8, 18, NULL, '2022-07-12', '8484', 'Deputy Director Human Resources', 'Executive Director Forestry', 'Head Office', 'Forestry', 'Warning letter for SMN', 'Major', '<p>On 30th June 2022 during the weekly HR meeting, there was a discussion by (MD, DDHR, and EDF) regarding the response to the SMN warning letter. However, there was no clear communication by the EDF to HO Nursery Manager and he asked him to seek an explanation from the DDHR on what was expected.</p>', 'closed', '2022-07-22', '2022-08-01', '2022-10-14', '2022-10-31', '2022-10-14', 'This was addressed in the working party.', '<div>1. All staff must have notebooks in meetings, discussions, or interactions. However, this has already been addressed in the working party to follow up on the implementation.</div>', '<div>1. Communications related to HR that affect the daily work are also the responsibility of HODs, It is wrong to disassociate such issues and direct them to DDHR when the answer is simple. DDC and DDHR will address this during the working party.<br>2. Response from the auditee should not take over 8days like the case for this CAR.</div>', '<div>To be addressed at the working party.</div>', NULL, '2022-07-12 19:39:55', '2022-11-22 20:47:15'),
(448, 19, 11, 9, 8, 19, NULL, '2022-07-12', '3319', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer Nyongoro', 'Site Manager Plantation Nyongoro', 'Nyongoro', 'Forestry', 'Task management', 'Major', '<p>Employee clocked in for an activity &nbsp;he did not do.</p><p>10072022-Hashako (pms) was clocked in watering moringa and did collection of mulch and mulching of moringa. No manual watering was done for moringa. Watering results were awarded and recorded.&nbsp;</p><p>It as been raining hence the ground was still wet and there was no need for watering.&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2022-07-14', '2022-07-18', '2022-10-17', '2022-11-17', '2022-10-14', 'The site manager for plantations shall get a warning letter.', '<div>1. This is lack of ownership and responsibility that ultimately led to lack of communication and mortality in the field.<br>2. We shall initiate a record for the changes of the day between the front office and the back offfice and signed by the head office managers. Effective week of 21st Nov 2022.<br><br>NB: the CAR shall be printed and attached to the warning letter and also to be used as a reference for evaluations.<br><br></div>', '<div>The company provides airtime to site responsibles to enable timely communication at all times. Someone is most definitely not taking their job seriously.</div>', '<div>The site plantations manager and HO plantation manager shall both get a warning for lack of taking responsibility and effectively communicating for change in task.<br>15/09/2022 Verbal written warning was given by EDF to the Site plantations manager and HO Plantations manager on 25th July 2022.</div>', '<div>1. Relevant parts of the corrective actions need to be attached to warnings<br>2. Records of changes in the back office based on changes on the ground shall be provided starting next week and put in the document control.<br>3. Monitoring and evaluation shall check if these changes are being implemented</div>', '2022-07-13 01:26:31', '2023-02-22 17:00:32'),
(449, 28, 28, 29, 5, 18, NULL, '2022-07-13', '2815', 'Site Logistic Manager Dokolo', 'Site Logistic Manager Dokolo', 'Dokolo', 'Operations', 'PPE Management Policy', 'Major', '<p>Shortage and Worn out PPEs&nbsp;</p><p>It is observed that the PPE status at the site (PPE store) is poor.&nbsp;</p><p>All casual workers gumboots are torn, 35 out of 73 green overalls in the PPE store are torn.</p><p>Some Riding suits torn, 3 helmets (glasses broken) and gloves are also torn.</p><p>Site lacks chemical sprayers\' PPEs.</p><p>Security uniforms also wearing out (trousers are losing the black colour).&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2022-07-15', '2022-07-18', '2022-07-20', '2022-07-27', '2022-07-20', NULL, '', '<div>Same response as 9733</div>', '<div>Same response as 9733</div>', NULL, '2022-07-13 21:30:20', '2022-09-15 15:38:17'),
(450, 32, 15, 10, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-07-14', '3206', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks 2', 'Forest Technician Kiambere', 'Kiambere', 'Forestry', 'Improved seedling production Job card 2022', 'Minor', '<p>Inadequate space in a job card.</p><p>Job card has inadequate space to fill daily water consumption in the experiment.An exercise book has been used to record the quality of water used to water the &nbsp;seedlings in the experiment.</p><p>M&amp;E observed this on 21/6/22 in kiambere site.</p><p>FT is responsible to ensure that a job card has an adequate space to record the &nbsp;quantity of water used to &nbsp;water seedlings.</p>', 'closed', '2022-07-14', '2022-07-18', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '<div>&nbsp;ICT is developing a comprehensive electronic job card.</div>', '<div>This shows there is no proper supervision by the HO manager as he should check and identify such areas during his review.<br>On CAR 3813 it was noted that the seedlings are dying every week and this is one of the causes, the seedlings are not properly watered.<br><br><br></div>', NULL, '2022-07-14 06:12:37', '2022-09-15 15:35:40'),
(451, 28, 28, 29, 5, 28, NULL, '2022-07-15', '9733', 'Site Logistic Manager Dokolo', 'Site Logistic Manager Dokolo', 'Dokolo', 'Operations', 'PPE Management Policy', 'Major', '<p>Shortage and Worn out PPEs</p><p>It is observed that the workers\' PPE status at the site is poor.</p><p>13 pairs of gumboots are torn and 35 out 73 green overalls for casual workers in the PPE store are torn.</p><p>3 riding jackets are torn, 4 riding jackets have spoilt zips, 4 riding trousers are torn, 3 riding helmets (glasses are broken).</p><p>site lacks chemical spraying PPEs like facemasks, rubber gloves and goggles.</p><p>security uniforms wearing out (6 trousers losing the black colour, 3 shirts lost the green colour, and 3 caps lost the black colour).</p>', 'closed', '2022-07-15', '2022-07-21', '2022-10-17', '2022-12-31', '2022-10-14', 'We agree with the HR', '<div>This is being addressed between FOD and HR and schedules will be part of next years budgets.</div>', '<div>The longterm solutions will be addressed by DDHR and MD</div>', '<div>We shall plan, budget, and replace different categories of PPEs according to the list of PPEs for all the sites. The replacement period shall be specific depending with the use and the category.<br>The site responsibles should ensure proper maintenance,issuance and storage of the PPEs.<br><br></div>', '<div>We have worked on the final schedules that will reflect in the budget and will address all issues with PPE.</div>', '2022-07-15 14:38:20', '2023-01-24 14:39:58'),
(452, 28, 28, 29, 5, NULL, NULL, '2022-07-18', '4718', 'Site Logistic Manager Dokolo', 'Site Logistic Manager Dokolo', 'Dokolo', 'Operations', 'Housekeeping Checklist', 'Major', '<p>Unwashed Drinking water tank</p><p>It is observed that the site drinking water tank was not cleaned and refilled with clean water on 15/07/2022 as it should have been done.</p><p>The communication for not cleaning the tank on the said day was not given to the Operations Manager earlier.</p>', 'closed', '2022-07-22', '2022-07-26', NULL, NULL, '2022-07-20', 'The corrective action proposed is wrong. We only have one activity in Dokolo and the SLM has failed to supervise.\nCorrect and resubmit', '', '<div>Clean drinking water is essential to the workers; when something goes wrong, it should be communicated immediately, and possibly upfront before there is no water.</div>', '<div>There is a procedure in place that has to be followed at all times.</div>', NULL, '2022-07-18 14:37:41', '2022-09-15 15:40:25'),
(453, 16, 22, 29, 5, 19, NULL, '2022-07-21', '485', 'Deputy Director Human Resources', 'Site logistics Manager Nyongoro', 'Nyongoro', 'Operations', 'Feedback by Nyongoro SLM on HOS and his Assistant  Performance', 'Major', '<p>According to the feedback by SLM, the HOS and his assistant have improved their performance from last time\'s evaluation. However, they are not yet up to their task as the supervisors who are in charge of the security team. E.g they are not firm when managing their team and many guards have developed a mindset that there is not much work on site.</p>', 'closed', '2022-07-25', '2022-07-27', '2022-10-17', '2022-11-17', '2022-10-14', '1. The HOS and assistant \n2. We will hire a Security Officer who has a better understanding on security management.', '<div>The HOS shall be someone at the level of a manager who can manage the security. The two HOS and his assistant will be released of their tasks.</div>', '<div>Vertical and cross communication&nbsp;<br>The key is leading by example, workers look up to their bosses, if they are not assertive or use the \'\'temporary no forestry activities\'\' as a reason to relax all workers will do the same.</div>', '<div>Implementation of the leadership quality and measuring of the results required.</div>', NULL, '2022-07-21 18:05:58', '2022-11-29 16:53:50'),
(454, 2, 13, 8, 8, 28, NULL, '2022-07-21', '6678', 'Monitoring and Evaluation Officer Dokolo', 'Site Manager Dokolo site', 'Dokolo', 'Forestry', 'Partner Farmer\'s hard copy contract', 'Major', '<p>162 partner farmers have no hard copy contracts</p><p>During M&amp;E farmer tree count verification, MEOs observed that 162 farmers spread across Dokolo District had no hard copy contracts although had planted.&nbsp;</p><p>This was observed during the farmer verification from week 52 (2021) to week 15 (2022)</p>', 'closed', '2022-07-22', '2022-08-04', '2022-10-17', '2022-12-31', '2022-10-14', 'Printed by accounts and distributed when AAs start visiting the farmers.', '<div>This is being worked on by accounts and M&amp;E.<br>1. By next week all the contracts should be delivered.</div>', '<div>See DDHRs comment.</div>', '<div>To be addrressed by Forestry department.However,any report shared might be used by management to make a decision and every staff has to take responsibility of their work and ensure any information shared is correct at all times.Also,the supervisors should review the reports and approve.</div>', '<div>The capture app should be ready end of this week, we must finalise the farmers contract, upload and the AAs ca start using it.</div>', '2022-07-21 20:19:05', '2023-03-23 14:54:53'),
(455, 28, 28, 29, 5, 28, NULL, '2022-07-22', '608', 'Site Logistic Manager Dokolo', 'Site Logistic Manager Dokolo', 'Dokolo', 'Operations', 'Site Infrastructures', 'Major', '<p>Cracked structure walls and detached roof</p><p>During a routine inspection on the site structures at the Nursery in week 29, it was observed by MEO (SLM) that the latrine curtain wall has cracks by the doors and the workers\' shade\'s grass thatched roof is detaching.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2022-07-22', '2022-07-26', '2022-10-17', '2022-10-31', '2022-10-14', '1. This took long to see these cracks and that is the responsibility of SLM to make sure the assigned company property is maintained and communicate as well as you are daily.\n2. Add to Maintenance APP.', '<div>These Structures have been added to the preventive Maintenance.<br>SLM to do the repairs ASAP</div>', '<div>Vertical communication&nbsp;<br>Use of the maintenance App for follow-up on infrastructure.</div>', '<div>Agree with DDC\'s comment above.<br>The SLM is in charge of all the company property on site and has to take responsibility for ensuring everything is in good condition and well maintained at all times. Not to wait until things get worse.</div>', '<div>This has been well addressed in matters of systems and will be addressed in the WP and meetings on staff awareness. Staff to be critical (measure the performance of the systems and give suggestions for improvement) when using systems and understand the human intervention is key in our operations.</div>', '2022-07-22 04:08:28', '2023-01-24 14:45:43'),
(463, 1, 5, 1, 5, 18, NULL, '2022-07-22', '7295', 'Information Security Manager', 'FOD & Quality Coordinator', 'Head Office', 'Operations', 'test', 'Minor', '<p>test</p>', 'closed', '2022-07-22', '2022-07-22', '2022-08-08', '2022-08-09', '2022-08-04', 'TEST', '', '<div>Test<br>No response needed</div>', '<div>Test<br>No response needed</div>', NULL, '2022-07-22 19:39:00', '2022-08-10 14:12:51'),
(464, 32, 35, 29, 5, 32, NULL, '2022-07-24', '9479', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks 2', 'Site Manager Farmers Programme 7Forks', '7 Forks', 'Operations', 'Certificate of registration of work place-7Forks office.', 'Minor', '<p>An expired certificate of registration of work place.The certificate is for 7Forks,and it expired on 30/6/22.</p><p>M&amp;E observed in week29(21/7/22).</p><p>SMFP who is responsible communicated and shared a photo of the certificate with OM but certificate renewal has not been done.</p><p>Below is the attached evidence.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2022-07-25', '2022-07-27', '2022-10-21', '2022-10-31', '2022-10-14', 'Renewals should be done way in advance before the expiry. e.g 2 months.\nPut in place a Schedule or task for the renewal of all licences in the company indicating when the renewal should happen.', '<div>There is a system now to apply for all company certficate renewals 1 month in advance. There is also a schedule with expiry dates.</div>', '<div>Vertical comunication.<br>A list of all licenses should be compiled and added to the task manager to ensure a reminder is sent before the due date. To ensure timely renewals by the Operations manager.</div>', '<div>Reoccurrence will be a human resource issue.</div>', '<div>Use of outlook.</div>', '2022-07-25 00:22:38', '2023-01-24 14:48:30'),
(465, 8, 15, 10, 8, 32, NULL, '2022-07-25', '3813', 'Executive Director Forestry', 'Forest Technician Kiambere', 'Kiambere', 'Forestry', 'Kiambere Nursery weekly stock report (Week 18 to week 22)', 'Major', '<p>There has been a consistent loss of seedlings in the Kiambere nursery (the trial on improved seedling production). Despite this, there has been no justifiable cause of mortality nor an appropriate strategy to stop the loss of seedlings put in place.&nbsp;</p><p>Our objective is to have zero mortality.</p><p>Summary of the weekly figures below:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>wk18</td><td>wk19</td><td>wk20</td><td>wk21</td><td>wk22</td><td>wk23</td><td>wk24</td><td>wk25</td><td>wk26</td><td>wk27</td><td>wk28</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 1,111.00&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 1,083&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;1,070&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;1,070&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 1,058&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 1,052&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 1,028&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;1,012&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;990&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;954&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 937&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', 'closed', '2022-07-26', '2022-08-01', '2022-10-24', '2022-11-08', '2022-10-14', 'The FT shall get a warning for handling the whole experiment wrongly. ', '<div><br>1. The Ft and PM must do things right at first (focus on preventive measures to avoid occurrences rather than putting actions in place after occurrences)<br>2. Daily control:- the FT must critically check continuously within his work domain if everything is ok.<br>3. Daily communication on-site activities between the head office and the site must be done. At the end of the day, there must be a daily report.</div>', '<div>Vertical communication<br>1. This should have photos attached.<br>2. This shows untimely communication, as any seedling dying shows a lack of prevention which again is handled through communication.<br>3. A mortality rate of 16% in a week should be a major concern that has daily or even more than once a day communication with the head office involving the HO manager and the HOD.&nbsp;</div>', '<div>Leadership might be an issue here and failure to take responsibility.</div>', '<div>1. This is a lack of proper and timely communication. If there would have been timely communication on the situation then this would have been averted. This should be based on a checklist that is specific and precise.&nbsp;</div>', '2022-07-25 13:32:19', '2023-02-22 17:01:33'),
(466, 19, 11, 9, 8, 19, NULL, '2022-07-26', '2321', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer Nyongoro', 'Site Manager Plantation Nyongoro', 'Nyongoro', 'Forestry', 'Nursery infrastructure', 'Major', '<p>Crossing over nursery fence</p><p>It was noted with great concern that we have a clique of PMSs on site that have made it a habit of crossing over the nursery fence instead of accessing the nursery through the gate like everybody else. This is a report that has been brought forward in two consecutive days(25th July and 24th July 2022) by the HOS. All employees on site have been informed previously to desist from malicious activities including crossing over the fence especially now when we’re establishing a live fence. This behavior is causing the company time and money in doing repairs on the fence wires which cannot be tolerated further. &nbsp;Below find the names of the people involved;&nbsp;</p><ol><li>Ali Guyo.</li><li>Abdullah Salim.</li><li>Suleiman Hashako.</li><li>Gideon Benjamin</li></ol>', 'closed', '2022-07-26', '2022-07-27', '2022-10-17', '2022-10-31', '2022-10-14', 'was addressed. ', '<div>1. The staff who crossed over through the fence got warning letters.&nbsp;</div>', '<div>See response on 1783</div>', '<div>Damage to the company property is unacceptable as it cost the company.Disciplinary measures shall be administered.</div>', '<div>1. We will enhance the nursery fence with Chain link and barbed wire.<br><br></div>', '2022-07-26 11:30:20', '2023-02-22 17:01:56'),
(467, 19, 22, 29, 5, 19, NULL, '2022-07-26', '1783', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer Nyongoro', 'Site logistics Manager Nyongoro', 'Nyongoro', 'Operations', 'Nursery infrastructure', 'Major', '<p>Crossing over nursery fence</p><p>It was noted with great concern that we have a clique of PMSs on site that have made it a habit of crossing over the nursery fence instead of accessing the nursery through the gate like everybody else. This is a report that has been brought to forward in two consecutive days(25th July and 24th July 2022) by the HOS. All employees on site have been informed previously to desist from malicious activities including crossing over the fence especially now when we’re establishing a live fence. This behavior is causing the company time and money in doing repairs on the fence wires which cannot be tolerated further. &nbsp;Below find the names of the people involved;&nbsp;</p><ol><li>Ali Guyo.</li><li>Abdullah Salim.</li><li>Suleiman Hashako.</li><li>Gideon Benjamin</li></ol>', 'closed', '2022-07-27', '2022-07-29', '2022-10-17', '2022-10-31', '2022-10-14', '1. The staff involved received a warning.\n2. We Keep monitoring any malicious damage to company property.\n3. Sensitize the workers on handling company property.', '', '<div>Vertical communication.<br>This was properly addressed by operations.</div>', '<div>Damage to the company property is unacceptable as it cost the company.Disciplinary measures shall be administered.&nbsp;</div>', NULL, '2022-07-26 11:30:20', '2022-11-29 16:59:40'),
(468, 32, 15, 29, 5, 32, NULL, '2022-07-28', '8954', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks 2', 'Forest Technician Kiambere', 'Kiambere', 'Operations', 'Stock management', 'Major', '<p>Pipe number 195 is missing in the nursery.The pipe was being used in the nursery watering system.</p><p>This was observed on 28/7/2022.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2022-07-30', '2022-08-01', '2022-10-04', '2022-10-31', '2022-09-30', '1. To have a permanent fence and gate in the nursery (in progress)\n2. Security patrols and extra vigilance on property on site.\n3. Close supervision of security and monitoring of site staff', '<div>This has been reported and police did investigation and we never got the thieves.<br>Moving forward, whenever we lay pipes to the plantation, we will take stock, marked, indicated and stock has to be taken when we bring the pipes to the nursery and put them back to stock.</div>', '<div>Vertical communication:&nbsp;<br>The site responsibles to communicate to all workers that theft harms the company and by extension themselves. It also reflects poorly on the community around the plantation.</div>', '<div>Theft is gross misconduct and unacceptable by the company. Each and every occurrence shall be investigated and disciplinary measures administered to the culprits.&nbsp;</div>', NULL, '2022-07-28 20:12:24', '2022-11-29 17:08:19'),
(469, 32, 15, 29, 5, 32, NULL, '2022-07-28', '4886', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks 2', 'Forest Technician Kiambere', 'Kiambere', 'Operations', 'Collection of fencing materials', 'Minor', '<p>An activity was done without a work instruction.</p><p>Collection of fencing materials was done in compartment A016 on 28/7/2022 and the work instruction for the activity was not provided by FT.The M&amp;E had already shared to the FT the list of reference documents required for monitoring on 21/7/2022.</p><p>Below are the PMS doing the activity.</p>', 'closed', '2022-07-30', '2022-08-01', '2022-10-04', '2022-10-31', '2022-09-30', '1. I agree with Communication.\n2. the NC should be on Work done and reference should be on work instruction', '', '<div>Vertical communication: This is untimely communication<br><br></div><div>Not all activities need work instructions however, it is at the time of planning the activity that communication should happen between the site and the planners at the head office. Some activities might require additional information or training. This must be assessed before the start of the activity. The absence of W.I. at the start of an activity should not be used as a reason why it is not done or done properly. Lack of understanding is only one phone call away.<br><br></div>', '<div>Agree with DDC comment above</div>', NULL, '2022-07-29 02:44:19', '2022-11-29 17:10:02'),
(470, 32, 15, 29, 5, 18, 305, '2022-08-02', '4940', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks 2', 'Forest Technician Kiambere', 'Kiambere', 'Operations', 'Forestry Site Tasks/Task rates 30th July to 5th Aug.', 'Minor', '<p>Approved Forestry and Operations week31 plan was not pinned on kiambere\'s notice board.</p><p>Monitoring and Evaluation Officer observed this on 2/8/22.</p><p>Attached is a weekly plan for week30 on the notice board.</p>', 'closed', '2022-08-04', '2022-08-12', '2022-10-11', '2022-10-31', '2022-09-30', '1. The FT should have followed up immediately, which is the responsible thing to do to get his work done.\n2. Raise a CAR to accounts for delaying the payment.', '', '<div>all the above answers show a complete lack of communication.&nbsp;</div>', '<div>We have a problem with the FT Kiambere</div>', NULL, '2022-08-02 14:29:51', '2022-11-29 17:10:48'),
(471, 32, 15, 29, 5, 32, 310, '2022-08-02', '7797', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks 2', 'Forest Technician Kiambere', 'Kiambere', 'Operations', '20430 KIA-Perm-Maint-Fencing.', 'Minor', '<p>An activity was done without a work instruction.</p><p>In week31 fencing was done in compartment A016 on 2/8/2022 and the work instruction for the activity was not provided by FT. The M&amp;E had already shared to FT the list of reference document required for monitoring on 31/7/2022.</p><p>This was observed by MEO on 2/8/2022 in kiambere site.</p><p>A similar CAR was raised in week30.</p><p>Attached is the PMs in full PPE doing the activity.</p>', 'closed', '2022-08-04', '2022-08-12', '2022-10-04', '2022-10-31', '2022-09-30', '1. Agree with Communication. \n2. MEO to share work schedule a day before she goes to KIA with time lines when she intends to interact with FT', '', '<div>Not all activities need WI or PR.&nbsp; Where is common sense and in case of doubts communication with the supervisor?</div>', '<div>Agree with DDC comment above</div>', NULL, '2022-08-02 18:44:23', '2022-11-29 17:11:09'),
(472, 16, 8, 8, 8, 18, NULL, '2022-08-04', '1905', 'Deputy Director Human Resources', 'Executive Director Forestry', 'Head Office', 'Forestry', 'PPE policy implementation', 'Major', '<p>According to the policy, all staff should clock in after they are issued with the right PPEs by the SLM or site responsible. Upon checking the employee attendance records for all the sites for the period July 1st to 27th, it was clear that the policy has not been adhered to. In all the sites, the junior staff arrives and clocks in earlier than the site responsibles.</p>', 'closed', '2022-09-06', '2022-09-14', '2022-10-17', '2022-10-24', '2022-10-14', 'Refer to the above HOD comments.', '<div>To redo the non-conformance and address it to the site responsibles who are/were late.</div>', '<div>No response from the manager.</div>', '<div>To be addressed by EDF and MD</div>', NULL, '2022-08-04 18:21:54', '2023-01-26 18:56:03'),
(473, 16, 5, 29, 5, 18, NULL, '2022-08-04', '9389', 'Deputy Director Human Resources', 'FOD', 'Head Office', 'Operations', 'PPE policy implementation', 'Major', '<p>According to the policy, all staff should clock in after they are issued with the right PPEs by the SLM or site responsible. Upon checking the employee attendance records for all the sites for the period July 1st to 27th, it was clear that the policy has not been adhered to. In all the sites, the junior staff arrives and clocks in earlier than the site responsibles.</p>', 'closed', '2022-08-11', '2022-08-12', '2022-10-11', '2022-10-14', '2022-09-30', '1. To close this CAR and raise again a new CAR to the Site responsible.', '', '<div>No response from the manager.</div>', '<div>To be addressed by FOD and MD</div>', NULL, '2022-08-04 18:21:55', '2022-11-29 17:11:53'),
(474, 32, 35, 8, 8, 32, 327, '2022-08-05', '4386', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks 2', 'Site Manager Farmers Programme 7Forks', '7 Forks', 'Forestry', 'Group sensitation report wk25', 'Minor', '<p>A BGF farmer group has not been issued with BGF certificate.</p><p>In week31 M&amp;E physically interviewed 4 farmers of Kaliani Tree Planting Self Help Group in Kyuso ward Maseki sublocation and they confirmed that they have not been issued with BGF certificate.</p><p>Attached below is their names.</p>', 'closed', '2022-08-10', '2022-08-17', '2022-10-24', '2023-01-31', '2022-10-14', 'We shall issue certificates once we reactivate the groups', '<div>1. This is an ongoing activity and shall be addressed once we resume the group activation exercise.&nbsp;</div>', '<div>no response from the manager</div>', '<div>To be addressed between HOD and MD</div>', '<div>1. There is a communication issue. The procedure shall be issued to the whole team who will sign that they have read and understood. The copy shall also be put in their files.<br>2. Groups certificates will be printed as we reactivate them.&nbsp;</div>', '2022-08-06 01:46:23', '2023-03-23 15:18:18'),
(475, 8, 9, 8, 8, 18, NULL, '2022-08-08', '7976', 'Executive Director Forestry', 'Plantation Manager', 'Head Office', 'Forestry', 'Establishment plan for trial (improved seedling production) seedlings', 'Minor', '<p>During the review of the plan for establishing seedlings in the KIA nursery, it was agreed their watering will be done by both the donkey cat (1 cat with two donkeys) and the remaining donkeys (3 donkeys) to improve efficiency and save costs. However, this was not the case during implementation. The donkey cat was not used.&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2022-08-10', '2022-09-14', '2022-10-17', '2022-10-31', '2022-10-14', '. The FT to get a warning. ', '<div>1. Failure to implement approved plans.<br>2. lack of taking responsibilty.<br>3. The plantations manager shall get a warning from HR.</div>', '<div>No response from the manager</div>', '<div>There are a lot of things that have gone wrong in this trial and both the FT and HO Plantations manager should get a warning as its unacceptable.</div>', '<div>1. The plantation manager did not analyse critically the information used for the planning. He must also at all times follow up and ensure implementation is according to plan.</div>', '2022-08-08 19:33:39', '2023-03-23 15:07:57'),
(476, 8, 15, 9, 8, 32, NULL, '2022-08-08', '2281', 'Executive Director Forestry', 'Forest Technician Kiambere', 'Kiambere', 'Forestry', 'Establishment of trial (improved seedling production) seedlings', 'Minor', '<p>It was agreed that each donkey would transport five jerricans of water each from the dam to the establishment area. However, it was seen in pictures during the implementation that each donkey was transporting only 4 jerricans.</p>', 'closed', '2022-08-10', '2022-08-11', '2022-10-24', '2022-11-11', '2022-10-14', 'The FT to get warning letter. ', '<div>1. Lack of communication by the FT to the supervisor.<br>2. Lack of supervision by the FT.</div>', '<div>This communication is essential as it affects task rates and consequently workers\' bonuses.</div>', '<div>What has the leave policy have to do with donkeys carrying 4 jerrycans instead of 5?</div>', '<div>1. The head office manager must follow up and ensure that plans are implemented as approved. this was a clear lack of following instructions and follow-up.&nbsp;</div>', '2022-08-08 19:50:03', '2023-03-23 15:06:02'),
(477, 8, 9, 8, 8, 19, NULL, '2022-08-08', '5069', 'Executive Director Forestry', 'Plantation Manager', 'Head Office', 'Forestry', 'Establishment of trial (improved seedling production) seedlings', 'Minor', '<p>It was agreed that each donkey would transport five jerricans of water each from the dam to the establishment area. However, it was seen in pictures during the implementation that each donkey was transporting only 4 jerricans.</p>', 'closed', '2022-08-11', '2022-09-14', '2022-10-17', '2022-10-31', '2022-10-14', '1. The Forest Technician and the Plantations manager to get a warning.', '<div>1. Lack of follow-up &amp; supervision by the plantations\' manager.&nbsp;</div>', '<div>managers response is missing.</div>', '<div>Change of a task has implications on the work and the reward of the workers and can\'t be taken lightly.</div>', '<div>1. lack of communication to indicate that there are changes in activities during the day.<br>2. The template for changes shall be used starting next week after being sent to the document app.</div>', '2022-08-08 19:50:04', '2023-03-23 15:06:56'),
(478, 8, 15, 9, 8, 32, NULL, '2022-08-08', '9244', 'Executive Director Forestry', 'Forest Technician Kiambere', 'Kiambere', 'Forestry', 'Plan for establishment of trail (improved seedling production) seedlings. ', 'Major', '<p>As seen in the pictures, the selection of the seedlings was done poorly. some of the seedlings planted do not even have leaves.</p>', 'closed', '2022-08-10', '2022-08-11', '2022-10-24', '2022-11-14', '2022-10-14', 'Refer to  the HOD comment above. ', '<div>1. The FT did not supervise the activity.<br>2. The Ft will get a warning letter.&nbsp;<br><br></div>', '<div>lack of communication in both directions between forest technician and plantations manager.</div>', '<div>Agree with DDC comment</div>', '<div>1. The personnel responsible, though aware of the requirements for seedlings election still went ahead and selected bad seedlings for planting. We need better supervision on site and staff that take responsibility and ownership.&nbsp;</div>', '2022-08-08 19:57:45', '2023-03-23 15:09:46'),
(479, 8, 9, 8, 8, 32, NULL, '2022-08-08', '8436', 'Executive Director Forestry', 'Plantation Manager', 'Head Office', 'Forestry', 'Plan for establishment of trail (improved seedling production) seedlings. ', 'Major', '<p>As seen in the pictures, the selection of the seedlings was done poorly. some of the seedlings planted do not even have leaves.</p>', 'closed', '2022-08-11', '2022-09-14', '2022-10-04', '2022-10-31', '2022-09-30', 'The FT should implement the work instructions and supervise as required. This is also being addressed by the job-card.', '<div>1. The cause by the auditee does not address the root cause.&nbsp;<br>2. The activity was not supervised by the FT.<br>3. There was no supervision by the plantations\' manager.</div>', '<div>There is no response from the manager</div>', '', '<div>the manager of the plantation, should review all the activities or actions. This was not done before for the seedling selection</div>', '2022-08-08 19:57:46', '2023-03-23 15:10:59'),
(480, 8, 15, 9, 8, 32, NULL, '2022-08-08', '8924', 'Executive Director Forestry', 'Forest Technician Kiambere', 'Kiambere', 'Forestry', 'Establishment of trial seedlings (improved seedling production)', 'Major', '<p>Watering was done before the half-moons were made. Half-moons are made immediately after the seedling is planted to prevent the water from flowing away on a sloppy surface.&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2022-08-10', '2022-08-11', '2022-10-24', '2022-11-11', '2022-10-14', '1. The Forest technician to get a warning for negligence.', '<div>1. Lack of supervision by the FT while the activity of planting was being done.</div>', '<div>Work instructions are there for a reason. FT should explain why he does not follow them. Supervisors are supposed to lead by example!!!</div>', '<div>See comment on 4974</div>', '<div>1. The team that did establishment was not well trained and supervised to ensure that they were doing the correct thing.<br>2. The head office manager did not do his job by checking if activities of establishment were being done correctly</div>', '2022-08-08 20:00:09', '2023-03-23 15:12:01'),
(481, 8, 9, 8, 8, 32, NULL, '2022-08-08', '4974', 'Executive Director Forestry', 'Plantation Manager', 'Head Office', 'Forestry', 'Establishment of trial seedlings (improved seedling production)', 'Major', '<p>Watering was done before the half-moons were made. Half-moons are made immediately after the seedling is planted to prevent the water from flowing away on a sloppy surface.&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2022-08-10', '2022-09-14', '2022-10-04', '2022-10-31', '2022-09-30', '1. The FT must implement the work instructions and supervise as required.', '<div>1. We have updated work instructions on site both in hard copy and soft copy.<br>2. The Ho manager must at all times follow up on a daily basis to check if activities have been done appropriately or not for immediate action.<br>3. This therefore means that the HO manager failed to properly supervise the implementation of the project.&nbsp;</div>', '<div>There is no response from the manager</div>', '<div>This is a communication problem between the FT and HO plantations manager.</div>', '<div>1. lack of communication to indicate that there are changes in activities during the day.<br>2. The template for changes shall be used starting next week after being sent to the document app.</div>', '2022-08-08 20:00:11', '2023-03-23 15:12:30'),
(482, 8, 15, 9, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-08-08', '381', 'Executive Director Forestry', 'Forest Technician Kiambere', 'Kiambere', 'Forestry', 'Leave Policy', 'Major', '<p>If a staff member works on Sunday at the site, he/she is supposed to take a compensation leave immediately after on the next Monday to allow them to rest. This decision was also taken by the site technician without consultation. However, this was not the case for:</p><ol><li>a. Munenei Kayalo worked on 31st July was supposed to take leave on 1st August 2022. but has now applied for the same compensation leave for 13th August 2022</li><li>b. Mathitu Joseph Mwendwa worked on 26th july 2022 and was supposed to take compensation on 27th July 2022 but has now applied for the same compensation leave to be taken on 11th August 2022</li><li>c. masavi Shadrack munyoki worked on 31st july and was supposed to take compensation leave on 1st August but has applied to take the compensation on12th August 2022.</li><li>&nbsp;</li></ol>', 'closed', '2022-08-10', '2022-08-11', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '<div>see comment on 2303</div>', '', NULL, '2022-08-08 21:00:53', '2022-09-15 16:04:20'),
(483, 8, 9, 8, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-08-08', '2158', 'Executive Director Forestry', 'Plantation Manager', 'Head Office', 'Forestry', 'Leave Policy', 'Major', '<p>If a staff member works on Sunday at the site, he/she is supposed to take a compensation leave immediately after on the next Monday to allow them to rest. This decision was also taken by the site technician without consultation. However, this was not the case for:</p><ol><li>a. Munenei Kayalo worked on 31st July was supposed to take leave on 1st August 2022. but has now applied for the same compensation leave for 13th August 2022</li><li>b. Mathitu Joseph Mwendwa worked on 26th july 2022 and was supposed to take compensation on 27th July 2022 but has now applied for the same compensation leave to be taken on 11th August 2022</li><li>c. masavi Shadrack munyoki worked on 31st july and was supposed to take compensation leave on 1st August but has applied to take the compensation on12th August 2022.</li><li>&nbsp;</li></ol>', 'closed', '2022-08-11', '2022-09-14', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '<div>see comment on 2303</div>', '', NULL, '2022-08-08 21:00:58', '2022-09-15 16:03:57'),
(484, 8, 10, 10, 8, 18, NULL, '2022-08-08', '2303', 'Executive Director Forestry', 'Head Office Nursery Manager', 'Head Office', 'Forestry', 'Leave Policy', 'Major', '<p>If a staff member works on Sunday at the site, he/she is supposed to take a compensation leave immediately after on the next Monday to allow them to rest. This decision was also taken by the site technician without consultation. However, this was not the case for:</p><ol><li>a. Munenei Kayalo worked on 31st July was supposed to take leave on 1st August 2022. but has now applied for the same compensation leave for 13th August 2022</li><li>b. Mathitu Joseph Mwendwa worked on 26th july 2022 and was supposed to take compensation on 27th July 2022 but has now applied for the same compensation leave to be taken on 11th August 2022</li><li>c. masavi Shadrack munyoki worked on 31st july and was supposed to take compensation leave on 1st August but has applied to take the compensation on12th August 2022.</li><li>&nbsp;</li></ol>', 'closed', '2022-08-10', '2022-08-10', '2022-10-01', '2022-10-14', '2022-09-30', '1. The staff should follow the leave policy.\n2. The FT should implement the policy correctly. ', '<div>1. The leave policy has been explained several times to all permanent staff both through the HR department and within the department. This is therefore staff are aware of the leave policy at all levels.<br>2. Since staff are aware of the policy, if a leave applied contravenes the policy then it shall simply be declined either by the HOD or HR depending on the type of leave and days deducted as stipulated by the HR policy.</div>', '<div>Communications and human resource policies should be part of the training manuals from forestry and operations and signed to avoid staff saying they were not aware or ignore them.</div>', '<div>Agree with DDC comment above.<br>Leave policy has been severally communicated to all staff, including during site visits by the mgt team. If staff does not comply then the HOD should decline the leave and the day deducted.</div>', '<div>1. Schedule for compensation has been put in place because it is known in advance when a staff will work over the weekend or holiday<br><br></div>', '2022-08-08 21:00:58', '2023-03-23 15:16:40');
