(485, 18, 15, 29, 5, 18, NULL, '2022-08-31', '5229', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer HO', 'Forest Technician Kiambere', 'Kiambere', 'Operations', 'Security', 'Major', '<p>On 26/08/2022,the FT Kiambere sent a security guard (Mathews Munyoki) to Ngungani police station without approval from HR and no communication was made.</p><p>Evidence: The section in the OB for Mathew Munyoki\'s occurrences was not recorded.</p>', 'closed', '2022-09-01', '2022-09-06', '2022-10-01', '2022-10-14', '2022-09-30', '1. FT to always follow instructions as given. To deliver letters as asked.\n2. See approval to changes on instructions given unless it is a critical activity that requires initiative.', '', '<div>Wrong cross-communication. The head of security is to accept instructions from the Forest technician only if they are within the company policy and communicate them with his supervisor.</div>', '<div>There is no excuse you don\'t send a security guard to do the job that should be done by the site responsible. The problem also is the conflict between the FT and the HOS.<br>FT&nbsp; got a&nbsp; second warning.<br><br></div>', NULL, '2022-08-31 13:27:50', '2022-11-29 17:12:29'),
(486, 8, 15, 9, 8, 32, NULL, '2022-09-14', '9241', 'Executive Director Forestry', 'Forest Technician Kiambere', 'Kiambere', 'Forestry', 'Kiambere permanent maintenance stock records (PMF)', 'Major', '<ol><li>Out of the 875 seedlings planted in A016 in week 31, 42 seedlings are already dead. In the records, there is also no explanation of the root cause. This is contrary to the survival policy of zero mortality.</li></ol>', 'closed', '2022-09-16', '2022-09-16', '2022-10-01', '2022-10-14', '2022-09-30', 'The FT shall get warning letter.\nThere must be daily reporting from site before they leave the office.', '<div>1. The FT and the head office manager for plantations need to put the correct root causes and the correct corrective action.<br>2. Communication:- The head office manager must have systems in place to verify the field reports on a daily basis.&nbsp;</div>', '<div>Seedlings should be monitored every day all the time and any signs of suffering should be communicated immediately(Timely communication). If this was done action would have been taken immediately and there would be zero mortality.</div>', '<div>The HOD should not approve any leave to any of the sites responsible if any critical activity is ongoing. Unless if it\'s an emergency and in this case there should be proper planning and communication to ensure everything is done effectively.&nbsp;</div>', '<div>1. Points to need for better supervision while the activity is happening.<br>2. Thorough reviews of the data at the end of the day.<br>3. Spot checks by the site supervisor against the results given.<br>4. Better planning to ensure everything/resources needed have been considered.&nbsp;</div>', '2022-09-14 13:31:38', '2023-03-23 16:02:07'),
(487, 19, 11, 9, 8, 19, NULL, '2022-09-28', '6838', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer Nyongoro', 'Site Manager Plantation Nyongoro', 'Nyongoro', 'Forestry', 'PMF as at (Week 27, 30, 35 and 36), Forestry tree counting forms data for (A016 and A066)', 'Major', '<p>The manual tree count report of A016 and A066(13th June 2022 and 21st June 2022) respectively &nbsp;is not what is reported in the PMF of the respective weeks(27, 30, 35 and 36)</p><p><br>In the manual report forms, compartment A016 has 3033 trees while PMF has 2610 trees resulting to variance of 423 trees.&nbsp;</p><p>In the manual report forms, compartment A066 has 5482 trees while PMF has 5288 trees resulting to variance of 194 trees.&nbsp;</p><p><br>In the manual report forms for A066 the data written on the forms does not match with the data verified in the forms. Data on the form is 5502 trees while data contained in the forms is 5482 trees.</p><p><br>There is no comment or explanation on either the forms or the PMF regarding the differences in the tree stocks.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2022-09-28', '2022-09-28', '2022-10-01', '2022-10-14', '2022-09-30', 'Both the head office Plantations Manager and the Site Manager Plantations shall get warning letters for dishonesty. ', '<div>Both the site manager and the head office managers\' responses are not close to adequate. They are excuses for not doing what is required of them. The site manager must communicate figures as they are, the head office manager needs as part oof his job to be critical when he recieves these reports, ask questions and ensure that there are explanations that justify the variations. This will form the basis of whether the job needs to be redone to get the correct figures.&nbsp;</div>', '<div>It is the job of the site responsible to communicate the right figures, Considering that we are dealing with biological assets that do not belong to BGF this should be reported to HR</div>', '<div>Sharing wrong figures shows that the manager is not taking the job seriously and shall be addressed by the HOD.</div>', '<div>1. The site managers are responsible for the end results. They are the ones that should put the results in the back office.<br>2. The manuals shall be reviewed to aclearly outline individual responsibilities of the forestry personnel</div>', '2022-09-28 11:55:42', '2023-03-23 15:17:12'),
(488, 32, 35, 29, 5, 32, 671, '2022-10-05', '705', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks 2', 'Site Manager Farmers Programme 7Forks', '7 Forks', 'Operations', 'Preventive maintenance application.', 'Minor', '<p>The manual preventive maintenance checklist of machineries that were filled by Agroforestry agents on 4/10/22 were not updated in the preventive maintenance application on 4/10/22.</p><p>SMFP said, ``Operation manager did not approve preventive maintence of machineries that i booked on 3/10/22\".</p><p>Below is attached evidence.</p>', 'closed', '2022-10-05', '2022-10-11', '2022-10-24', '2022-11-04', '2022-10-14', '1. We need to have time frames and communicated to the teams\n2. Put this on the notice board', '<div>This will be addressed electronically through the IT department, to have AAs schedule check their motorbikes in the app instead of sending manual checklists to the SMFP&nbsp;<br>A ticket has been made.</div>', '<div>Timely communication and follow-up</div>', '<div>Nothing from HR.</div>', '<div>This will be addressed electronically through the IT department, to have AAs schedule check their motorbikes in the app instead of sending manual checklists to the SMFP&nbsp;<br>A ticket has been made.</div>', '2022-10-05 13:53:35', '2023-01-24 14:54:56'),
(489, 18, 7, 5, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-10-11', '844', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer HO', 'Accounts Manager', 'Head Office', 'Accounts', 'Delayed payment-CAR 4940', 'Minor', '<p>Delayed payment that led to Operations/Forestry week 30 plan not to be printed and pinned on Kiambere\'s notice board.</p><p>FT\'s comment “ The cash request for printing was done 2 weeks prior”</p>', 'closed', '2022-10-13', '2022-10-17', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div>1. This is purely lack of communication and planning on the FT and the account manager.<br>2. Lack of responsibility, follow up and ignorance by the FT.<br>3. This has been followed up and not happening anymore.</div>', '<div>Making an IPR does not mean you sit and wait. Following up is also critical</div>', '<div>Lack of communication is unacceptable.</div>', '<div>1. This is purely lack of communication and planning on the FT and the account manager.<br>2. Lack of responsibility, follow up and ignorance by the FT.<br>3. This has been followed up and not happening anymore.</div>', '2022-10-11 13:40:54', '2023-01-26 19:44:51'),
(490, 16, 5, 29, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-10-13', '6068', 'Deputy Director Human Resources', 'FOD', 'Head Office', 'Operations', 'Kiambere site visit report on 4th and 5th October', 'Major', '<p>Lack of proper implementation of PPE policy: The PPEs put in sacks are mixed and the majority of them are dirty and disorganized. Also, no labels to show what type of PPEs is inside each sack.</p>', 'closed', '2022-11-14', '2022-11-18', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div>To be added to the house keeping schedule and monitored by the FT<br>To make a wooden basket for dirty PPE<br>Check for inclusion in the PPE policy.<br><br></div>', '<div>See Hr comment&nbsp;</div>', '<div>We need to have somebody on permanent basis to be doing the housekeeping task.</div>', '<div>To be addressed in the WP.</div>', '2022-10-13 18:17:49', '2023-03-23 15:23:32'),
(491, 16, 5, 29, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-10-13', '8860', 'Deputy Director Human Resources', 'FOD', 'Head Office', 'Operations', 'Kiambere site Visit Report 4th and 5th October 2022', 'Major', '<p>Employees changing rooms: After employees change into the company PPEs, some leave their home clothes in the changing rooms. This is hygienically wrong as different staff clothes mix and also it might lead to someone losing their items.</p>', 'closed', '2022-11-14', '2022-11-18', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div>Operations will make a structure on the wall of the PPE store for workers to hang their clothes.<br>To be done within 2 weeks.</div>', '<div>Operations to advise&nbsp;</div>', '<div>To be addressed by FOD to have a possibility of having a place where workers can keep their home clothes.</div>', '<div>Operations will make a structure on the wall of the PPE store for workers to hang their clothes.<br>To be done when funds are available.<br>OM to raise an IPR</div>', '2022-10-13 18:28:17', '2023-03-23 15:30:29'),
(492, 16, 5, 29, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-10-13', '5707', 'Deputy Director Human Resources', 'FOD', 'Head Office', 'Operations', 'Kiambere site Visit Report 04th and 5th October 2022', 'Major', '<p>Drinking water tank: The drinking water tank has not yet been properly repaired as there is still water leakage.</p>', 'closed', '2022-11-16', '2022-11-18', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '<div>This shows lack of timely communication. It should have been communicated the moment it was discovered there was&nbsp; leakage and repaired</div>', '<div>Drinking water is essential to all workers and has to be well managed at all times.</div>', '', '2022-10-13 18:42:22', '2023-03-23 15:25:07'),
(493, 16, 5, 29, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-10-13', '8498', 'Deputy Director Human Resources', 'FOD', 'Head Office', 'Operations', 'Kiambere site Visit Report 04th and 5th October 2022', 'Major', '<p>Torches for use at night: Most guards have challenges with their torches not lasting with power for long while on patrols at night.&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2022-11-14', '2022-11-18', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div>Addressed</div>', '<div>Addressed</div>', '<div>Addressed</div>', '<div>Addressed</div>', '2022-10-13 18:45:49', '2023-03-23 15:26:25'),
(494, 16, 5, 29, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-10-13', '6068', 'Deputy Director Human Resources', 'FOD', 'Head Office', 'Operations', 'Kiambere site Visit Report 04th and 5th October 2022', 'Major', '<ol><li>PPE Policy implementation: According to the policy, the FT should ensure all the PPEs are in good condition including security uniforms. If any needs repair he organizes and gets them repaired. However, during our meeting, while on-site, the security guards made us aware that the HOS instructed them to come with needles and do the repairs e.g. Makua Maithya confirmed to repair his uniform.</li></ol>', 'closed', '2022-11-14', '2022-11-18', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div>Addressed</div>', '<div>Addressed</div>', '<div>.Addressed</div>', '<div>Addressed</div>', '2022-10-13 18:56:49', '2023-03-23 15:28:15'),
(495, 4, 15, 29, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-10-14', '3886', 'Deputy Director Communications', 'Forest Technician Kiambere', 'Kiambere', 'Operations', 'Kiambere site visit', 'Major', '<p>In week 40 we visited the Kiambere site and discovered some expired chemicals, the SLO seemed unsure on what action to take.</p>', 'closed', '2022-10-18', '2022-10-27', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div>The procedure is done and shared.<br>FT does not read the work instructions</div>', '<div>Timely communication is essential in both ways. Possibly an App for expired chemicals and licenses?</div>', '<div>1.Expired chemicals that are not disposed are a hazard to workers and its unacceptable. They should be disposed immediately.</div><div><br></div><div>2.Maybe a stock management app that mentions the expiry date can help.</div><div><br><br></div>', '<div>Do checks when on site.<br>Send a mail to FT<br>Add a column for expiry date for chemicals for weekly stock reports</div>', '2022-10-14 20:34:50', '2023-03-23 15:36:45'),
(496, 4, 15, 29, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-10-14', '3892', 'Deputy Director Communications', 'Forest Technician Kiambere', 'Kiambere', 'Operations', 'Week 40 Kiambere Site Visit', 'Major', '<p>Drinking water tank: The drinking water tank has two taps. It’s not very clear which tap should be used.</p>', 'closed', '2022-10-17', '2022-10-18', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div>Addressed</div>', '<div>The solution was long overdue.&nbsp;</div>', '<div>The workers have a right to use clean water at all times. Possibly buy drinking water.</div>', '<div>Addressed</div>', '2022-10-14 20:46:55', '2023-03-23 15:37:22'),
(497, 4, 15, 29, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-10-14', '7885', 'Deputy Director Communications', 'Forest Technician Kiambere', 'Kiambere', 'Operations', 'Kiambere Site visit Week40', 'Major', '<p>There was a PMS who had gotten an eye injury and he complained that he was told to walk to the hospital, whereas some staff are taken to the hospital on a motorbike.</p>', 'closed', '2022-10-17', '2022-10-18', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div>To be addressed in the WP</div>', '<div>The eye injury was communicated on time. Some measures will be adapted for continuous improvement.</div>', '<div>We need to have an occurrence book on site where after any accident/incident the injured worker shall sign that they are okay to resume work.<br><br></div><div>On the first Aid procedure, we shall adopt that based on the nature of the injury a decision shall be taken together with the worker and the site responsible on whether to use the motorbike or not.</div>', '<div>To be addressed in the WP</div>', '2022-10-14 20:54:45', '2023-03-23 15:40:09'),
(498, 32, 15, 9, 8, 32, NULL, '2022-11-04', '1411', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks 2', 'Forest Technician Kiambere', 'Kiambere', 'Forestry', 'TREE COUNTING (COMPARTMENT STOCK ASSESSMENT)WORK INSTRUCTION. REV.220222.', 'Minor', '<p>Boundary of compartment A004 is not correctly marked.Two rows at one side of the periphery of the compartment have been marked using paints hence difficult to differentiate which row act as the boundary.</p><p>M&amp;E observed this while doing stock verification in compartment A004 on &nbsp;01/11/ 2022 .</p>', 'closed', '2022-11-07', '2022-11-08', '2023-01-24', '2023-02-28', '2023-01-20', '1. Lack of prospection of compartments.\n2. poor communication.\n3. This shall be corrected by getting the right staff.', '<div>1. there are weekly planning meetings based on checks of the areas the activities shall be carried out. It is therefore clear that these checks are not done or if they are done then they are not sufficient.&nbsp;<br><br></div>', '<div>Emphasis on timely communication. &nbsp;</div>', '<div>Agree with DDC comment</div>', '<div>We shall put this activity in the maintenance activity as something that has to be redone when the paint dissappears or get washed away by rains.&nbsp;</div>', '2022-11-04 21:16:37', '2023-03-23 15:42:35'),
(499, 18, 15, 9, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-11-16', '5938', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer HO', 'Forest Technician Kiambere', 'Kiambere', 'Forestry', 'PMF week 42,M&E  week 45 report.', 'Major', '<p>Tree count variation of 75 trees in compartment A005 that was counted by Forestry in week 23 and verified by M&amp;E in week 45.</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Compartment</td><td>FOR count</td><td>M&amp;E count</td><td>Variance</td></tr><tr><td>A005</td><td>2752</td><td>2677</td><td>75</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2022-11-17', '2022-11-18', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div>the prospection activity was either not done or done properly to ensure that everything is ok before commencement of the tree counting activity.&nbsp;</div>', '<div>There is a communication problem. staff must communicate when resources/needed input is missing before doing a task. there should have been communication that some rows had not been marked.&nbsp;</div>', '<div>Planning has to be prioritized and coordinated between the site responsibles and the HO Managers.</div>', '<div>marking of rows shall be introduced in the maintenance app.</div>', '2022-11-16 20:10:16', '2023-03-23 15:52:12'),
(500, 18, 11, 9, 8, 18, NULL, '2022-11-16', '4779', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer HO', 'Site Manager Plantation Nyongoro', 'Nyongoro', 'Forestry', 'PMF week 42,M&E week 45 report.', 'Major', '<p>Tree count variation of 273,414 and 88 trees between Forestry count and M&amp;E count in compartments C011,D014 and F028 respectively.</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Compartment</td><td>FOR count</td><td>M&amp;E count</td><td>Variance</td><td>FOR week</td><td>M&amp;E week</td></tr><tr><td>D014</td><td>2947</td><td>2533</td><td>414</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>44</td></tr><tr><td>C011</td><td>3015</td><td>3288</td><td>-273</td><td>12</td><td>43</td></tr><tr><td>F028</td><td>4810</td><td>4722</td><td>88</td><td>42</td><td>45</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', 'closed', '2022-11-18', '2022-11-21', '2023-01-24', '2023-02-24', '2023-01-20', '1. Poor supervision of the tree counting activity. This is because boundaries have been marked but we still get variances.\n2. We are working on getting the right staff in the right positions.', '<div>Has been addressed</div>', '<div>The variances are too huge, this should have raised an alarm bell to the supervisors and the HO manager.</div>', '<div>All this are reasons why not and its unacceptable. This shows the SMP and HOPM are not doing their job.</div>', '<div>Prospection is done before activity planning.</div>', '2022-11-16 20:39:48', '2023-03-23 15:54:28'),
(501, 32, 15, 9, 8, 32, 1059, '2022-11-22', '4961', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks 2', 'Forest Technician Kiambere', 'Kiambere', 'Forestry', 'TREE COUNTING (COMPARTMENT STOCK ASSESSMENT)WORK INSTRUCTION.', 'Minor', '<p>Row 16&amp;23 in compartment A008 have been marked with the same row number hence misleading in determining the number of rows in the comparment.</p><p>M&amp;E observed this while doing stock verification on 22nd Nov 2022.</p>', 'closed', '2022-11-24', '2022-11-25', '2023-01-24', '2023-02-28', '2023-01-20', '1. Poor supervision by the site head.\n2. We are working on getting the right staff in the right positions.', '<div>Addressed</div>', '<div>Lack of supervision.&nbsp;</div>', '<div>Poor supervision when the teams are in the field by the FT&nbsp;</div>', '<div>Prospection is done before activity planning</div>', '2022-11-23 00:15:49', '2023-03-23 15:56:04'),
(502, 32, 35, 8, NULL, NULL, 1074, '2022-11-25', '2648', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks 2', 'Site Manager Farmers Programme 7Forks', '7 Forks', 'Forestry', 'Group sensitization report Wk 44.', 'Major', '<p>BGF farmers group &nbsp;by the name Kalamba Mukau Growers has not been registered with the ministry of social services.</p><p>Kalamba Mukau Growers is in Kyandali sublocation Mumoni ward.</p><p>This was observed by M&amp;E while doing group verification on 25th of Nov 2022.</p>', 'closed', '2022-11-28', '2023-03-08', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div>It has been addressed</div>', '<div>communication issue. the site manager was not conversant with the process of group formation.</div>', '<div>See comment on CAR 7248</div>', '<div>it has been addressed.&nbsp;</div>', '2022-11-26 04:11:41', '2023-03-23 15:57:54'),
(503, 32, 35, 8, NULL, NULL, 1075, '2022-11-25', '7248', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks 2', 'Site Manager Farmers Programme 7Forks', '7 Forks', 'Forestry', 'Group sensitization report Wk 44.', 'Major', '<p>A BGF farmer group by the name Kalamba Mukau Growers in Mumoni ward,Kyandali sublocation has not been issued with BGF &nbsp;certificate.</p><p>This was observed by M&amp;E while doing group verification on 25th of Nov 2022</p>', 'closed', '2022-11-28', '2023-03-08', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div>This has been addressed.</div>', '<div>The issue of groups not meeting the requirements should be raised to the management team so the right action can be taken and the issues resolved.</div>', '<div>Agree with DDC comment.</div>', '<div>groups are being issued with certificates as we reactivate them.&nbsp;</div>', '2022-11-26 04:30:10', '2023-03-23 16:00:19'),
(504, 18, 11, 9, 8, 18, NULL, '2022-12-06', '8477', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer HO', 'Site Manager Plantation Nyongoro', 'Nyongoro', 'Forestry', 'Site task results, back end task results.29/11/2022 & 5/12/2022', 'Minor', '<p>Different task results between manual site results and back end results for M&amp;E tree counting that was done on 29th November 2022, and Manual cleaning that was done on 5th December 2022.</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>Site results</td><td>Back end results</td></tr><tr><td>29/11/2022</td><td>M&amp;E tree counting</td><td>Trees</td><td>1158</td><td>1156</td></tr><tr><td>5/12/2022</td><td>Manual cleaning</td><td>Ha</td><td>0.18</td><td>1.86</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', 'closed', '2022-12-07', '2022-12-08', '2023-01-23', '2023-02-28', '2023-01-20', '1. Poor supervision by the site responsible. \n2. To work on getting the right staff in the right position', '<div>weekly follow up by the M&amp;E.</div>', '<div>Timely and accurate communication is key.&nbsp;</div>', '<div>This is lack of taking responsibility by the SMP and its unacceptable. Also, sharing of wrong figures is a gross misconduct that warrants disciplinary measures.</div>', '<div>daily follow up by the HO managers to ensure the results are ok.</div>', '2022-12-06 16:39:09', '2023-03-23 16:01:27'),
(505, 18, 22, 29, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-12-06', '5806', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer HO', 'Site logistics Manager Nyongoro', 'Nyongoro', 'Operations', 'Site task results, back end task results.29/11/2022 & 5/12/2022', 'Minor', '<p>Different task results between manual site results and back end results for M&amp;E tree counting that was done on 29th November 2022 and Manual cleaning that was done on 5th December 2022.</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>Site results</td><td>Back end results</td></tr><tr><td>29/11/2022</td><td>M&amp;E tree counting</td><td>Trees</td><td>1158</td><td>1156</td></tr><tr><td>5/12/2022</td><td>Manual cleaning</td><td>Ha</td><td>0.18</td><td>1.86</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', 'closed', '2022-12-09', '2022-12-13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div>See forestry response. Manual Cleaning is a Forestry Activity</div>', '<div>Accurate figures &nbsp;<br>The effective delegation, you should only delegate approved tasks to the appropriate staff.</div>', '<div>This is lack of taking responsibility by the SLM and its unacceptable. Also, sharing of wrong figures is a gross misconduct that warrants disciplinary measures.</div>', '', '2022-12-06 16:39:11', '2023-04-13 14:50:48'),
(506, 19, 11, 9, 8, 19, NULL, '2022-12-08', '7700', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer Nyongoro', 'Site Manager Plantation Nyongoro', 'Nyongoro', 'Forestry', 'Health and Safety Policy', 'Major', '<p>Mechanical pruning team did not have full set of required PPE for the activity.</p><p>On 8/12/2022 at about 11.30am mechanical pruning team in D017 and C078 were not in full PPEs.</p><p>The missing PPEs for the team was gloves, 2helmets, 4 goggles, earmuffs and 5 reflectors.</p><p>The team consisted of 8 pms; Elijah Njoroge, Bakari Salim, Ronald Muhkwana, Shadrach Lughanji, Mtawali John, Omar Barisa, Hashako, and Daniel Okumu.</p><p>Gloves, Helmets, earmuphs and goggles are in stock as verified by M&amp;EO</p><p>The team did not pick all the required PPEs. They gave below reasons for not picking the PPEs</p><ol><li>The goggles retained sweat hence becoming uncomfortable to put on</li><li>The gloves are heavy and bulky</li><li>Reflectors are only 3</li><li>The helmet straps are faulty</li></ol>', 'closed', '2022-12-10', '2022-12-14', '2023-01-23', '2023-02-28', '2023-01-20', '1. Lack of proper supervision, coordination and communication between the site team. \n2. ', '<div>PPE replacement to be addressed.</div>', '<div>This should have been communicated and addressed in the planning meetings before the activity.</div>', '<div>This shows lack of supervision and taking responsibility by both the SLM and SMP.</div><div>Before any activity is done, there has to be an interaction with SMP and SLM ensure all the necessary tools and equipment are available and in good condition.</div><div>Also, as the supervisors they should ensure all the workers adhere to the company policies and procedures and if any does not comply communicate accordingly.</div><div>&nbsp;</div>', '', '2022-12-08 17:23:32', '2023-03-23 16:10:35'),
(507, 19, 22, 29, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-12-08', '989', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer Nyongoro', 'Site logistics Manager Nyongoro', 'Nyongoro', 'Operations', 'Health and Safety Policy', 'Major', '<p>Mechanical pruning team did not have full set of required PPE for the activity.</p><p>On 8/12/2022 mechanical pruning team in D017 and C078 were not in full PPEs.</p><p>The missing PPEs for the team was gloves, 2helmets, 4 goggles, earmuffs and 5 reflectors.</p><p>The team consisted of 8 pms; Elijah Njoroge, Bakari Salim, Ronald Muhkwana, Shadrach Lughanji, Mtawali John, Omar Barisa, Hashako, and Daniel Okumu.</p><p>Gloves, Helmets, earmuphs and goggles are in stock as verified by M&amp;EO</p><p>The team did not pick all the required PPEs. They gave below reasons for not picking the PPEs</p><ol><li>The goggles retained sweat hence becoming uncomfortable to put on</li><li>The gloves are heavy and bulky</li><li>Reflectors are only 3</li><li>The helmet straps are faulty</li><li>&nbsp;</li></ol>', 'closed', '2022-12-10', '2022-12-13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div>From now on we shall implement formally the procedures and instructions for use of PPEs. Workers will sign for training, explaining and understanding and any worker not wearing PPE more than once, shall face punitive measures to the extent of even dismisal.</div>', '<div>This should have been communicated and addressed in the planning meetings before the activity.</div>', '<div>This shows lack of supervision and taking responsibility by both the SLM and SMP.<br>Before any activity is done, there has to be an interaction with SMP and SLM ensure all the necessary tools and equipment are available and in good condition.<br>Also, as the supervisors they should ensure all the workers adhere to the company policies and procedures and if any does not comply communicate accordingly.</div>', '<div>OK</div>', '2022-12-08 17:23:33', '2023-04-13 14:57:47'),
(508, 16, 5, 29, 5, 19, NULL, '2022-12-08', '3779', 'Deputy Director Human Resources', 'FOD', 'Head Office', 'Operations', 'Nyongoro Site Visit Report 29th November to 02nd December 2022', 'Major', '<p>Lack of PPE Policy Implementation: During the visit we observed the below and it’s against the PPE policy;</p><p>1. Site staff change and put their home clothes in the PPE store.&nbsp;</p><p>2.Clean overalls and gumboots were mixed with dirty ones</p><p>3. Dirty safety boots with mold, mixed with new safety boots in a carton.</p><p>4.Overalls to be discarded were still hanged with clean PPEs</p>', 'closed', '2023-01-05', '2023-01-05', '2023-04-14', '2023-05-31', '2023-04-13', 'ok', '<div>We will construct an extension structure for storing home clothes<br>The Site Managers have to implement PPE policy to the latter.</div>', '<div>Poor leadership and taking responsibility</div>', '<div>Poor leadership/supervision and lack of taking responsibility. We need real site manager</div>', '<div>OK</div>', '2022-12-08 20:28:33', '2023-05-11 21:05:28'),
(509, 16, 5, 29, 5, 19, NULL, '2022-12-08', '8580', 'Deputy Director Human Resources', 'FOD', 'Head Office', 'Operations', 'Nyongoro site visit report (29th November to 02nd December 2022)', 'Major', '<ol><li>Housekeeping job card not implemented. There is no supervision hence the cleaning/arranging not properly done in different areas e.g., the offices and the store. Also, On 1st December in the afternoon, we found the housekeeper doing spot weeding, this was not part of the housekeeping tasks and yet her tasks were still not properly done.</li><li>&nbsp;</li></ol>', 'closed', '2023-01-05', '2023-01-08', '2023-04-14', '2023-05-31', '2023-04-13', NULL, '<div>We will hire on permanent basis at the level of PMS, Housekeepers at form 4 level who can read.<br>The Supervisors should supervise and check what the house keeper has done before signing the job card.</div>', '<div>There\'s a lack of supervision. We also need to hire a housekeeper who can read.</div>', '<div>Agree with Auditees comment.</div>', '<div>OK</div>', '2022-12-08 22:14:02', '2023-05-03 16:11:56'),
(510, 16, 5, 29, 5, 19, NULL, '2022-12-08', '1319', 'Deputy Director Human Resources', 'FOD', 'Head Office', 'Operations', 'Nyongoro Site Visit Report 29th November to 02nd December 2022', 'Major', '<p>We have three tents at the site, and all of them are not well maintained: Items were disorganized (the tent with security uniform), grass was overgrown near the tents, and all were torn in different areas and needs to be repaired.</p>', 'closed', '2023-01-05', '2023-01-08', '2023-04-14', '2023-05-31', '2023-04-13', NULL, '<div>The Tents are maintained like any other structure on site and added in the preventive maintenance app.<br>The Manage has to step up the maintenance of the site.<br>Agree with HR, we need a able Site manager.<br><br></div>', '<div>Poor leadership and ownership as the site responsible. The staff who sleep there should have communicated</div>', '<div>Poor leadership and taking responsibility. We need a real manager on site.</div>', '<div>OK</div>', '2022-12-08 22:37:16', '2023-05-11 21:04:59'),
(511, 16, 5, 29, 5, 19, NULL, '2022-12-08', '1797', 'Deputy Director Human Resources', 'FOD', 'Head Office', 'Operations', 'Nyongoro Site Visit Report 29th November to 02nd December 2022', 'Major', '<p>Security uniform not well maintained: The security uniforms were dirty, disorganized (some guards store their clothes in sacks), others&nbsp;hanged on the lines and the whole place looked untidy.&nbsp;<br>During the security meeting with OM while on site, they mentioned that their clothes get dusty and that\'s why they put them in sacks.</p>', 'closed', '2023-01-05', '2023-01-05', '2023-04-14', '2023-05-31', '2023-04-13', NULL, '<div>We have done an extension for the security office with shelves for each security to store their uniform.<br>The next is the maintenance of the security office which the SLR has to take up.<br>To be added to the preventive maintenance app.</div>', '<div>Poor leadership. Leadership comes with more responsibilities. Need to supervise and take ownership as the site responsible.</div>', '<div>Lack of supervision and implementation of housekeeping jobcard. SLM to get warning.</div>', '<div>OK</div>', '2022-12-08 22:47:12', '2023-05-11 21:04:39'),
(512, 16, 5, 29, 5, 19, NULL, '2022-12-08', '6292', 'Deputy Director Human Resources', 'FOD', 'Head Office', 'Operations', 'Nyongoro Site Visit Report 29th November to 02nd December 2022', 'Major', '<ol><li>Wrong location for Tractor Fire extinguishers: The tractor fire extinguishers were kept in the store instead of being at the tractors.</li></ol>', 'closed', '2023-01-05', '2023-01-08', '2023-04-14', '2023-05-31', '2023-04-13', NULL, '<div>To be fixed to each tractor.<br>To be followed up.</div>', '<div>Major nonconformance in case there was a fire.<br><br>See HR comment.</div>', '<div>Negligence and lack of taking responsibility by SLM, To get a warning.</div>', '<div>Also lack of communication as<br>1) At reception SLM should have communicated that the tractors need to be adapted<br>2) The tractor drivers should have complained that they are driving unsecured tractors for fire</div>', '2022-12-08 22:50:13', '2023-05-11 21:04:13'),
(513, 16, 5, 29, 5, 18, NULL, '2022-12-08', '1881', 'Deputy Director Human Resources', 'FOD', 'Head Office', 'Operations', 'Nyongoro Site Visit Report 29th November to 02nd December 2022', 'Major', '<p>Site supervisors (SLM, SNM and SMP) don\'t work as a team and support each other instead they keep focusing that they are in different departments.</p>', 'closed', '2023-01-05', '2023-01-08', '2023-02-01', '2023-03-01', '2023-01-20', 'It starts from the Head office Managers who do not work as a team.\nWe don\'t have the right people. \nWe need to have the right staff at all levels.', '<div>It starts from the Head office Managers who do not work as a team.<br>We don\'t have the right people.&nbsp;<br>We need to have the right staff at all levels.</div>', '<div>Different departments are supposed to support each other in the implementation as we are all working towards the same goals, mission and vision.<br><br></div>', '<div>Agree with the auditees comment.</div>', '<div>OK. Work in progress</div>', '2022-12-08 22:57:18', '2023-04-13 15:25:41'),
(514, 16, 8, 9, 8, 18, NULL, '2022-12-08', '5399', 'Deputy Director Human Resources', 'Executive Director Forestry', 'Head Office', 'Forestry', 'Nyongoro Site Visit Report 29th November to 02nd December 2022', 'Major', '<p>Site supervisors (SLM, SNM and SMP) don\'t work as a team and support each other instead they keep focusing that they are in different departments.</p>', 'closed', '2023-01-05', '2023-01-19', '2023-02-01', '2023-03-06', '2023-01-20', '1. To get the right people in the managerial positons who can communicate, workd as a team and ensure their staff do the same.', '<div>&nbsp;1. To get the right people in the managerial positons who can communicate, workd as a team and ensure their staff do the same.</div>', '<div>We all working in the same company towards the same mission and vision. We should work as a team and not focus that we are in different departments.</div>', '<div>Teamwork is critical. We still have rotten apples in our environment.&nbsp;</div>', '<div>OK</div>', '2022-12-08 22:57:18', '2023-04-13 15:26:20'),
(515, 16, 5, 29, 5, 19, NULL, '2022-12-08', '8230', 'Deputy Director Human Resources', 'FOD', 'Head Office', 'Operations', 'Nyongoro Site Visit Report 29th November to 02nd December 2022', 'Major', '<p>Time and attendance policy not implemented.<br>1.The random calls are answered when staff clock out and not when they happen reason being the HON has activities assigned and he can’t take the devices to workers by foot.&nbsp;</p><p>2. Sulubu (HON) was handling two devices reason being the other device handler was on leave and the SLM was busy.</p>', 'closed', '2023-01-05', '2023-01-05', '2023-01-23', '2023-04-03', '2023-01-20', 'The SLM to Delegate the task to the able security guards as per the attendance schedule for the time being until the security officer and 2 assistants have been recruited. By March 2023.\nHR to send a note to SLM.', '<div>The SLM to Delegate the task to the able security guards as per the attendance schedule for the time being until the security officer and 2 assistants have been recruited. By March 2023.<br>HR to send a note to SLM.</div>', '<div>See HR\'s comment</div>', '<div>The random calls has already been addressed.&nbsp;<br><br>It\'s the responsibility of the SLM to ensure the device handlers handle each device as allocated and approved.Incase somebody is not in, the SLM has to handle the device or delegate effectively.</div>', '<div>HR send a note to SLM.<br>we are in process of hiring Security officer and assistants; by March 2023</div>', '2022-12-08 23:04:23', '2023-01-24 14:59:31'),
(516, 16, 5, 29, 5, 19, NULL, '2022-12-08', '4118', 'Deputy Director Human Resources', 'FOD', 'Head Office', 'Operations', 'Nyongoro Site Visit Report 29th November to 02nd December 2022', 'Major', '<p>Lack of proper maintenance of company property;<br>1.The nursery beds were rusty due to unfavorable weather conditions<br>2.Pipes were not arranged in an orderly way.<br>3.Three tractors had worn out canopies.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2023-01-05', '2023-01-05', '2023-01-23', '2023-02-28', '2023-01-20', 'Warning was issued.\nTo have staff that have right attitude to the job as required.\nWe are Handling the problem with the SLM.\nThe OM to do follow ups as well as make site visits.', '<div>Warning was issued.<br>To have staff that have right attitude to the job as required.<br>We are Handling the problem with the SLM.<br>The OM to do follow ups as well as make site visits.</div>', '<div>This is a matter of taking ownership and responsibility as a person in charge of the site.</div>', '<div>This shows lack of taking responsibility by the SLM.</div>', '<div>This a continuous improvement related to HR; hiring the right people, training, and motivating staff and being careful in promoting.</div>', '2022-12-08 23:15:07', '2023-01-24 15:04:11'),
(517, 16, 5, 29, 5, 19, NULL, '2022-12-08', '4416', 'Deputy Director Human Resources', 'FOD', 'Head Office', 'Operations', 'Nyongoro Site Visit Report 29th November to 02nd December 2022', 'Major', '<ul><li>Blunt tools: The tools the PMS are issued with for use are blunt e.g., pruning saws and that makes them spend more energy and time on the same errand, and despite achieving the set target they get tired more quickly.</li></ul>', 'closed', '2023-01-05', '2023-01-05', '2023-01-23', '2023-02-28', '2023-01-20', 'Warning was issued.\nTo have staff that have right attitude to the job as required. by March 2023.\nOM to closely monitor all the machines in preventive maintenance.\n', '<div>Warning was issued.<br>To have staff that have right attitude to the job as required.</div>', '<div>Poor leadership.</div>', '<div>It\'s a hazard when workers use blunt tools that are not cutting properly. SLM not taking responsibility. A warning letter shall be issued.</div>', '<div>Strict use of the maintenance app and having the right people to give correct reports.<br>Proper supervision of the site activities at all levels.</div>', '2022-12-08 23:19:52', '2023-01-24 15:06:54'),
(518, 16, 5, 29, 5, 19, NULL, '2022-12-08', '3974', 'Deputy Director Human Resources', 'FOD', 'Head Office', 'Operations', 'Nyongoro Site Visit Report 29th November to 02nd December 2022', 'Major', '<p>Quality torches: During the site meeting Tabu Kazungu (security guard) requested for purchase of quality torches as the ones they have lasts with power for a maximum of one hour or less.&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2023-01-05', '2023-01-05', '2023-03-01', '2023-03-31', '2023-01-20', '\nWe need the have the right people. \nWe have started the process of reviewing the individual positions at all levels. To be completed by end of March 2023.\nMeanwhile, we will replace all the torches, by 3rd Feb.', '<div>We will have a strong Security officer to ensure proper management of the torches and function all the time.<br>To be in place in beginning of March.</div>', '<div>See HR\'s comment</div>', '<div>The problem is how the torches are maintained by the guards and supervision. We need strong supervision.</div>', '<div>See the HOD comment.</div>', '2022-12-08 23:24:02', '2023-01-24 15:08:16'),
(519, 16, 8, 9, 8, 19, NULL, '2022-12-08', '5475', 'Deputy Director Human Resources', 'Executive Director Forestry', 'Head Office', 'Forestry', 'Nyongoro Site Visit Report 29th November to 02nd December 2022', 'Major', '<p>Lack of supervision: The PMS informed us that there is no adequate supervision by the SMP and sometimes if they need some guidance, it becomes hard for them. If a mistake is done it is corrected later after some days and yet this could have been avoided/corrected immediately. This was confirmed by the SMP (during the meeting with site responsibles only), that sometimes he goes to the plantation twice per week due to lack of fuel for his motorbike.</p>', 'closed', '2023-01-05', '2023-01-19', '2023-01-23', '2023-02-28', '2023-01-20', '1. The head office manager must check on a daily basis and ensure that the Plantations manager is supervising the activities that had been planned. \n2. The head office manager must also go to site to check if things are in order.', '<div>1. The head office manager must check on a daily basis and ensure that the Plantations manager is supervising the activities that had been planned.&nbsp;<br>2. The head office manager must also go to site to check if things are in order.</div>', '<div>its the responsibility of the supervisor to be present and give feedback on the job done. Whether correctly or theres need to improve or rectify</div>', '<div>1.Workers are punished because of lack of leadership by the supervisor<br><br>2.The head office managers should constantly communicate with the site responsibles on daily basis and ensure everything is done correctly and on timely basis.</div>', '<div>At time of induction these items need to be clearly explained and staff have to sign they have understood</div>', '2022-12-08 23:31:19', '2023-05-11 21:03:51'),
(520, 4, 5, 29, 5, 19, NULL, '2022-12-13', '2438', 'Deputy Director Communications', 'FOD', 'Head Office', 'Operations', 'Nyongoro', 'Minor', '<p>The tent occupied by Rashid the tractor driver is due for repair</p>', 'closed', '2023-01-05', '2023-01-05', '2023-04-14', '2023-05-31', '2023-04-13', NULL, '<div>Addressed in another IPR<br>We need to have our own brick making machines to build our own site houses</div>', '<div>See HR\'s comment.</div>', '<div>SLM to get a warning letter.</div>', '<div>OK</div>', '2022-12-13 20:55:19', '2023-05-11 21:03:23'),
(521, 4, 8, 9, 8, 19, NULL, '2022-12-13', '5587', 'Deputy Director Communications', 'Executive Director Forestry', 'Head Office', 'Forestry', 'Nyongoro site visit', 'Major', '<ul><li>The plantation&nbsp;is very bushy and in desperate need of cleaning and pruning. It would be very easy for wild animals to hide there.</li></ul>', 'closed', '2023-01-05', '2023-01-19', '2023-01-25', '2023-02-28', '2023-01-20', '1. There should still be communication  on the state of the plantations even when the staff is limited and priorities can be agreed upon on which compartments need attention first to prevent hazards to workers.\n2. The head office managers need to be in the field to check what is going on.', '<div>1. There should still be communication&nbsp; on the state of the plantations even when the staff is limited and priorities can be agreed upon on which compartments need attention first to prevent hazards to workers.<br>2. The head office managers need to be in the field to check what is going on.</div>', '<div>To be addressed in broader context</div>', '<div>To be addressed in a broader context.</div>', '<div>Some planning to do here.</div>', '2022-12-14 01:58:17', '2023-05-11 21:02:19'),
(522, 4, 8, 9, 8, 18, NULL, '2022-12-13', '6024', 'Deputy Director Communications', 'Executive Director Forestry', 'Head Office', 'Forestry', 'Nyongoro site visit', 'Major', '<p>Communication barrier: Operations bought and delivered a rain gauge that the Nyongoro forester confirmed to be the wrong one, Even though the HO plantation manager had said it was okay.</p>', 'closed', '2023-01-05', '2023-01-19', '2023-01-25', '2023-02-28', '2023-01-20', '1. Specifications for all requisitions has to be there at all times.\n2. Better communication between Forestry and Operations at the head office and sites.', '<div>1. All details (including photos) for a tool/equipment should be provided to enable accurate procurement.<br>2. Before item is delivered to site it must be checked by forestry in the head office.</div>', '<div>when making an IPR give specifications of what you need and where possible one can include images</div>', '<div>Specifications for all requisitions has to be there at all times.</div>', '<div>Procedures to be (re)explained, understood and followed! Re-implementation to be done ASAP.&nbsp;</div>', '2022-12-14 02:20:28', '2023-04-13 15:40:38'),
(523, 4, 5, 29, 5, 18, NULL, '2022-12-13', '7206', 'Deputy Director Communications', 'FOD', 'Head Office', 'Operations', 'Nyongoro site visit', 'Minor', '<p>Site supervisors not understanding that they represent the company when talking to the workers.</p>', 'closed', '2023-01-04', '2023-01-05', '2023-04-17', '2023-05-31', '2023-04-13', NULL, '<div>1. Lack of strictness to implement company policies<br>2. it is a mind set problem with the managers</div>', '<div>Staff with higher positions need to practice responsible leadership.<br>They need to understand that they represent the company in all their dealings and act accordingly.</div>', '<div>We need strong site responsibles on top of what we have today.</div>', '<div>To be discussed in the Management team meeting.<br>At time of induction already staff need to be made aware that they represent the company.</div>', '2022-12-14 02:30:30', '2023-05-11 21:01:56'),
(524, 4, 8, 9, 8, 18, NULL, '2022-12-13', '2513', 'Deputy Director Communications', 'Executive Director Forestry', 'Head Office', 'Forestry', 'Nyongoro site visit', 'Minor', '<p>Site supervisors not understanding that they represent the company when talking to the workers.</p>', 'closed', '2023-01-05', '2023-01-19', '2023-01-25', '2023-02-28', '2023-01-20', '1. it is clear that punitive measures do not work anymore. The next stage is to have the right people in the right place. \n2. We have started the process of reviewing the individual positions at all levels and the deadline for implementing point 1 is the end of February.', '<div>1. it is clear that punitive measures do not work anymore. The next stage is to have the right people in the right place.&nbsp;<br>2. We have started the process of reviewing the individual positions at all levels and the deadline for implementing point 1 is the end of February.</div>', '<div>1. Staff with higher positions need to practice responsible leadership.<br>2. BGF staff need to understand that they represent the company in all their dealings and act accordingly.</div>', '<div>Every staff should positively represent the company at all times in their different roles. We should all ensure that we have positive mindset to grow in the company. We need to eliminate the rotten apples.</div>', '<div>Work here for DDC straight from induction.</div>', '2022-12-14 02:30:31', '2023-05-11 21:01:41'),
(525, 4, 5, 29, 5, 18, NULL, '2022-12-13', '2892', 'Deputy Director Communications', 'FOD', 'Head Office', 'Operations', 'Nyongoro site visit', 'Minor', '<ul><li>Lack of timely communication when planning the activities in far away compartments.</li><li>PMS expressed that sometimes they have to walk for over an hour to get to some compartments such that when they get there, they are already&nbsp;so tired and cannot be as productive and meet their target.</li></ul>', 'closed', '2023-01-04', '2023-01-08', '2023-01-20', '2023-02-20', '2023-01-20', 'We need the have the right people. \nWe have started the process of reviewing the individual positions at all levels. To be completed by end of March 2023.', '<div>We need the have the right people.&nbsp;<br>We have started the process of reviewing the individual positions at all levels. To be completed by end of March 2023.</div>', '<div>Vertical communication breakdown that should be addressed and rectified immediately.</div>', '<div>1.This shows poor planning and leadership by the site responsibles.&nbsp;<br>2.Lack of implementation of the procedure for tasks adjustments to ensure realistic targets are set, this allows temporary workers to get bonuses after they exceed the target and it\'s proven that job was properly done.&nbsp;</div>', '<div>see HOD comment</div>', '2022-12-14 02:41:37', '2023-01-24 15:17:25');
INSERT INTO `audits` (`id`, `user_id`, `response_id`, `manager_id`, `hod_id`, `followup_id`, `checklist_id`, `date`, `number`, `auditor`, `auditee`, `site`, `department`, `clause`, `checkbox`, `report`, `status`, `response_date`, `manager_date`, `followup_date`, `followup_end_date`, `hod_date`, `comment`, `mt_comment`, `communication_comment`, `hr_comment`, `final_comment`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(526, 4, 8, 9, 8, 18, NULL, '2022-12-13', '5304', 'Deputy Director Communications', 'Executive Director Forestry', 'Head Office', 'Forestry', 'Nyongoro site visit', 'Minor', '<ul><li>Lack of timely communication when planning the activities in far away compartments.</li><li>PMS expressed that sometimes they have to walk for over an hour to get to some compartments such that when they get there, they are already&nbsp;so tired and cannot be as productive and meet their target.</li></ul>', 'closed', '2023-01-05', '2023-01-19', '2023-01-24', '2023-02-24', '2023-01-20', '1. At this point, punitive measures do not work. The next stage is to have the right people in the right place. \n2. We have started the process of reviewing the individual positions at all levels and the deadline for implementing point 1 is the end of March 2023.', '<div>1. At this point, punitive measures do not work. The next stage is to have the right people in the right place.&nbsp;<br>2. We have started the process of reviewing the individual positions at all levels and the deadline for implementing point 1 is the end of March 2023.</div>', '<div>Prior communication after prospection to enable correct tasks rate targets</div>', '<div>A worker can\'t be penalized because a compartment is very far, and the task rates are not adopted accordingly.</div>', '<div>Distance and time to be added in the compartments description</div>', '2022-12-14 02:41:38', '2023-05-11 21:01:02'),
(527, 16, 4, 4, 23, 18, NULL, '2022-12-16', '9312', 'Deputy Director Human Resources', 'Deputy Director Communications', 'Head Office', 'Communications', '2022 Performance evaluations', 'Major', '<p>During the analysis of the 2022 performance evaluations, we realized that if the company changed the plans, the departmental/individual quality objectives were not communicated, and plans adjusted accordingly. Consequently, most staff had not achieved their objectives.&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2023-01-04', '2023-02-14', '2023-03-14', '2023-12-31', '2023-03-06', 'is common sense', '<div>This needs to be addressed in a broader perspective:<br>- awareness in the WP that QObjective need to be known and might be dynamic<br>- capturing in the document control app with revision number changes when needed<br><br></div>', '<div>It is the responsibility of each staff member to amend their objectives when there are major changes and have them signed by their HOD.<br>Communications will be following up on the same.</div>', '<div>It\'s very important that adjustments are done otherwise the evaluations are done on the wrong objectives .</div>', '<div>OK, has been addressed. Now the monthly review to be implemented&nbsp;</div>', '2022-12-16 14:22:22', '2023-05-11 21:00:37'),
(528, 32, 35, 29, 5, 32, 1291, '2023-01-05', '657', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks 2', 'Site Manager Farmers Programme 7Forks', '7 Forks', 'Operations', 'Daily preventive maintenance application and 7F list of tools,machines and structures.', 'Major', '<p>Long handled and short handled pruning saws have not been scheduled in the preventive maintenance application by SLM in 7F.</p><p>All tools,machines and structures in site are suppose to be scheduled in preventive maintenance application.</p><p>This was observed by M&amp;E on 2023/01/05.</p>', 'closed', '2023-01-07', '2023-01-10', '2023-01-28', '2023-02-28', '2023-01-20', NULL, '<div>The tools were issued to groups. The frequency of checking the tools to be done when groups are visited. Forestry to plan and have all the tools checked when AAs visit the farmer groups. The same to be addressed through the group or the farmers contract.</div>', '<div>HOD will address it</div>', '<div>MD will address with HOD</div>', '<div>See HOD comment above</div>', '2023-01-06 02:51:56', '2023-01-24 15:18:54'),
(529, 19, 11, 9, 8, 19, 1298, '2023-01-06', '2576', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer Nyongoro', 'Site Manager Plantation Nyongoro', 'Nyongoro', 'Forestry', 'Mechanical pruning task rate', 'Major', '<p>Targets for mechanical pruning on 5th January, 2023 was not achieved.</p><p>The overall Target was 700trees and 670 trees were pruned in compartment A014. 2pms that is Mtawali Karisa and Omar Barisa achieved 90 and 80 trees respectively instead of 100trees each.&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2023-01-09', '2023-01-09', '2023-01-20', '2023-02-10', '2023-01-20', ' This is a communication issue. When the machines breakdown workers should be allocated a different task immediately.', '<div>1. This is a communication issue. When the machines breakdown workers should be allocated a different task immediately.</div>', '<div>An issue like this should be communicated immediately to the HO Manager.</div>', '<div>Probably workers did not achieve the targets due to lack of communication to the HO to adjust the tasks rate.</div>', '<div>Let\'s observe and measure the results of the measures. The mindset in matters of communications must change! DDC&nbsp; to continue working relentlessly on this!</div>', '2023-01-06 11:54:50', '2023-04-13 15:52:19'),
(530, 32, 15, 9, 8, 32, 1336, '2023-01-10', '3962', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks 2', 'Forest Technician Kiambere', 'Kiambere', 'Forestry', 'TREE COUNTING(COMPARTMENT STOCK ASSESSMENT) WORK INSTRUCTION.', 'Minor', '<p>Three out of seventy two verified rows in compartment A015 have not been marked which is against tree counting work instruction that says rows in a compartment must be marked.</p><p>M&amp;E observed this while doing stock verification on 10th January 2023.</p>', 'closed', '2023-01-12', '2023-01-13', '2023-01-20', '2023-02-10', '2023-01-20', 'We shall have more close supervision by Head office manager whos shall visit the site immediately to oversee the operations.', '<div>We shall have more close supervision by Head office manager whos shall visit the site immediately to oversee the operations.</div>', '<div>Seems like prior prospection was not done as per the procedure hence the wrong information was communicated.&nbsp;</div>', '<div>FT giving wrong communication of prospection and wrong figures is unacceptable as it costs the company money.</div>', '<div>This keeps coming back which shows staff still doesn\'t understnd the importance of the exercise</div>', '2023-01-11 04:19:21', '2023-04-13 15:56:52'),
(531, 18, 28, 29, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2023-01-12', '1158', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer HO', 'Site Logistic Manager Dokolo', 'Dokolo', 'Operations', 'Preventive maintenance report for 11/1/2023,list of tools, equipment &machines.', 'Minor', '<p>Tools, equipment,&amp; machines for Dokolo were not scheduled &nbsp;in the preventive maintenance application on 10th January 2023.The items were missing in the preventive maintenance report for 11th January 2023.</p>', 'closed', '2023-01-14', '2023-01-19', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '<div>Taking responsibility and ownership should be practiced at all times.</div>', '<div>Refusal&nbsp; by the SLM to schedule the machines shows lack of taking responsibility and its unacceptable. SLM to get a warning.</div>', '<div>HR to ask why tools that should make work and life easier are being resisted</div>', '2023-01-12 17:25:54', '2023-04-13 16:00:56'),
(532, 18, 22, 29, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2023-01-12', '3931', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer HO', 'Site logistics Manager Nyongoro', 'Nyongoro', 'Operations', 'Preventive maintenance report for 11/1/2023,list of tools, equipment &machines.', 'Minor', '<p>Tools, equipment,&amp; machines for Nyongoro were not scheduled &nbsp;in the preventive maintenance application on 10th January 2023.The items were missing in the preventive maintenance report for 11th January 2023.</p>', 'closed', '2023-02-10', '2023-02-10', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2023-01-12 17:28:49', '2023-05-11 15:13:24'),
(533, 18, 8, 9, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2023-01-25', '6692', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer HO', 'Executive Director Forestry', 'Head Office', 'Forestry', 'Back-end results, site results', 'Minor', '<p>Lack of taking responsibility for site results by site managers.</p><p>HO Plantation Manager\'s comment.</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Error occurrence during uploading of results by the device handler. FT to check once the results have been uploaded by the device handlers.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>The correct result achieved was 802, site results variance resulted due to unclear handwriting. Clarification was done before result entry and the discrepancies corrected immediately.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', 'closed', '2023-02-02', '2023-02-07', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2023-01-25 16:04:24', '2023-05-11 15:14:14'),
(534, 18, 15, 29, 5, 32, NULL, '2023-01-25', '4357', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer HO', 'Forest Technician Kiambere', 'Kiambere', 'Operations', 'PPE management policy', 'Major', '<p>While handling power saw on 25th January 2023,the operator(Kyalo Muneni) did not have all the required PPE as per the PPE management policy. The missing PPE were, goggles, nose mask and gloves.</p>', 'closed', '2023-01-26', '2023-01-31', '2023-04-18', '2023-05-31', '2023-04-13', NULL, '<div>1. The proposed corrective action does not address the root cause of the problem.&nbsp;<br>2. Create awareness on the importance of wearing PPEs in meetings with staff.<br>3. Sensitise workers on the different types of PPE and their uses in meetings with staff.</div>', '<div>It should be followed up to know if FT knows the health and safety measures that come with staff not wearing complete PPEs and the consequences in case of an accident.&nbsp;</div>', '<div>FT should&nbsp; ensure that all staff are issued with the right PPEs at all times. Emphasize on awareness on the importance of wearing the PPEs should be done to all staff</div>', '<div>Agreed with the proposed actions</div>', '2023-01-26 02:25:11', '2023-05-11 21:00:25'),
(535, 18, 29, 29, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2023-01-25', '6324', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer HO', 'Operations Manager', 'Head Office', 'Operations', 'PPE management policy', 'Major', '<p>While handling power saw on 25th January 2023,the operator(Kyalo Muneni) did not have all the required PPE as per the PPE management policy. The missing PPE were, goggles, nose mask and gloves.</p>', 'closed', '2023-01-26', '2023-01-26', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div>The proposed corrective action does not address the root cause of the problem.&nbsp;</div>', '<div>This does not address the cause or the root cause.</div>', '<div>This is not an answer to addressing the root cause and it shows nobody is taking responsibility</div>', '', '2023-01-26 02:28:19', '2023-05-11 15:16:26'),
(536, 23, 4, 4, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2023-01-26', '8303', 'Managing Director', 'Deputy Director Communications', 'Head Office', 'Communications', 'Not following procedures', 'Major', '<p>Asking service from IT without raising a ticket.<br>Loss of Outlook password resulting of IT sending confidential password to the wrong receiver.<br>Breach in security<br>&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2023-02-02', '2023-02-14', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2023-01-26 18:16:04', '2023-05-11 15:16:45'),
(537, 23, 1, 23, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2023-01-26', '7240', 'Managing Director', 'Information Security Manager', 'Head Office', 'IT', 'Nor following the ticketing system', 'Major', '<p>Sending of staff password to wrong person after staff request without ticket nor consultation with supervisor resulting in a security breach</p>', 'closed', '2023-01-26', '2023-03-06', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2023-01-26 18:19:56', '2023-05-11 15:17:09'),
(538, 19, 11, 9, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2023-01-31', '6986', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer Nyongoro', 'Site Manager Plantation Nyongoro', 'Nyongoro', 'Forestry', 'Staff Identification', 'Major', '<p>M&amp;EO observed that eight employees didn\'t have their national ID and Staff ID.</p><p>This was observed on 31st January 2023 in the Morning.</p><p>The 8 employees who didn\'t have the IDs were Daniel Okumu, Ali Guyo, Mtawali John, Hashako Albado, Issa Muhammed, Abdula Salim, Herbert Chobola and Walter Oduor.</p><p>The Names have been attached in the evidence section with specific documents that the employees didn\'t have.</p><p>Impact.</p><p>As a result of the current security status in the area it may be difficult for one to identify themselves or prove their identity hence may fall on the bad side of the law.&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2023-02-01', '2023-02-02', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2023-01-31 15:21:52', '2023-05-11 15:20:40'),
(539, 32, 15, 9, NULL, NULL, 1437, '2023-02-01', '7649', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer 7Forks 2', 'Forest Technician Kiambere', 'Kiambere', 'Forestry', 'TREE COUNTING(COMPARTMENT STOCK ASSESMENT)WORK INSTRUCTION.', 'Minor', '<p>Two out of 40 rows in compartment A018 have been marked with the same row number. Both rows are marked with row number 26.</p><p>M&amp;E observed this while doing stock verification on 31st January,2023.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', 'closed', '2023-02-02', '2023-02-03', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2023-02-01 14:03:40', '2023-05-11 15:21:07'),
(540, 18, 15, 29, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2023-02-03', '5906', 'Monitoring & Evaluation Officer HO', 'Forest Technician Kiambere', 'Kiambere', 'Operations', 'Crocodile Cage', 'Minor', '<p>Lack of taking responsibility of company\'s property (Crocodile cage) by FT Kiambere.</p><p>The crocodile cage was washed away by floods on 1st October 2022 and was found by HO NM on 3rd February 2023.</p>', 'closed', '2023-02-06', '2023-02-07', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2023-02-03 21:55:02', '2023-05-11 15:23:17'),
(541, 16, 5, 29, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2023-02-10', '1539', 'Deputy Director Human Resources', 'FOD', 'Head Office', 'Operations', 'Kiambere Field Report of 23rd to 5th January 2023', 'Major', '<p>Handling and maintenance of clocking devices: Device movement from main holding area to PPE store or Chemical store without pouch/cover</p>', 'closed', '2023-03-06', '2023-03-06', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div>This has been addressed.&nbsp;<br>The devices to assigned to device handler with serial number.</div>', '', '', '<div>This has been addressed.&nbsp;<br>The devices to assigned to device handler with serial number.</div>', '2023-02-10 14:05:22', '2023-05-11 15:26:13'),
(542, 16, 5, 29, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2023-02-10', '6726', 'Deputy Director Human Resources', 'FOD', 'Head Office', 'Operations', 'Kiambere Field Report of 23rd  to 5th January 2023', 'Major', '<ul><li>Workers clock in first before being issued with PPE.<ul><li>PPE are mostly issued&nbsp; and received back by PMS (Masyuko mostly)</li></ul></li></ul>', 'closed', '2023-03-06', '2023-03-06', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2023-02-10 14:07:37', '2023-05-11 15:28:09'),
